1
00:00:29,170 --> 00:00:30,476
Hello...

2
00:00:42,160 --> 00:00:43,835
There's nothing like it...

3
00:00:46,679 --> 00:00:47,840
Welcome.

4
00:00:58,830 --> 00:01:03,530
"Unintentional Love Story: The Movie"

5
00:01:07,312 --> 00:01:08,420
Manager Jeong.

6
00:01:08,445 --> 00:01:09,835
I found the artist, Yun Tae-jun.

7
00:01:09,860 --> 00:01:11,710
(Meeting)
Look into his background.

8
00:01:11,898 --> 00:01:14,101
Do whatever you can...

9
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:16,390
- Be thorough.
- Okay, I'll give it a shot.

10
00:01:16,611 --> 00:01:17,365
What's that supposed to be?

11
00:01:17,390 --> 00:01:18,100
Sir...

12
00:01:18,296 --> 00:01:19,601
You don't seem to have any employees.

13
00:01:19,625 --> 00:01:20,796
(Moon Jar Pottery)
I don't need any.

14
00:01:20,820 --> 00:01:22,626
What kind of part-time
job are you looking for?

15
00:01:22,650 --> 00:01:23,570
Is there something over there?

16
00:01:23,595 --> 00:01:26,375
Why do you want to work at Ju-heon's shop?

17
00:01:27,304 --> 00:01:28,360
What are you up to?

18
00:01:28,679 --> 00:01:29,850
Are you busy?

19
00:01:29,875 --> 00:01:31,515
Won-young started working here yesterday.

20
00:01:36,620 --> 00:01:37,750
That's not right.

21
00:01:37,968 --> 00:01:40,382
I only have one small request.

22
00:01:41,085 --> 00:01:42,170
Please, just hear me out.

23
00:01:43,546 --> 00:01:45,346
Didn't you say you
wanted to experience life?

24
00:01:45,820 --> 00:01:46,969
In this pottery class...

25
00:01:47,304 --> 00:01:49,171
I don't teach life lessons.

26
00:01:49,484 --> 00:01:52,078
Don't be too disappointed if
you come up empty-handed.

27
00:01:53,546 --> 00:01:54,630
Sir.

28
00:01:56,830 --> 00:01:58,031
I feel great.

29
00:02:00,010 --> 00:02:01,610
My heart almost skipped a beat just now.

30
00:02:01,859 --> 00:02:03,139
Please don't get the wrong idea.

31
00:02:03,193 --> 00:02:04,003
I won't.

32
00:02:04,028 --> 00:02:05,601
Ko Ho-tae!

33
00:02:08,742 --> 00:02:10,148
Hey, I told you not to touch that!

34
00:02:12,476 --> 00:02:13,546
Damn it.

35
00:02:13,571 --> 00:02:14,561
But still...

36
00:02:14,586 --> 00:02:17,316
Why are you so curious about Cha Ju-heon?

37
00:02:19,296 --> 00:02:20,976
I need to go check out some houses nearby.

38
00:02:21,101 --> 00:02:21,870
House hunting?

39
00:02:21,895 --> 00:02:23,755
Yes, for personal reasons.

40
00:02:23,890 --> 00:02:25,085
You're not even feeling well.

41
00:02:27,426 --> 00:02:28,426
Ji Won-young.

42
00:02:28,990 --> 00:02:29,990
Just come with me.

43
00:02:30,390 --> 00:02:31,578
Oh my god.

44
00:02:31,789 --> 00:02:33,726
I'm actually at Yun Tae-jun's house.

45
00:02:33,751 --> 00:02:35,179
This isn't a dream, is it?

46
00:02:35,233 --> 00:02:37,320
I need to find something to use as a lead.

47
00:02:37,345 --> 00:02:39,289
He's such an incredible person.

48
00:02:41,127 --> 00:02:42,204
I just need to put this on top.

49
00:02:42,228 --> 00:02:43,536
I told you to put it down.

50
00:02:46,175 --> 00:02:47,906
Are you feeling okay?

51
00:02:47,931 --> 00:02:50,211
- Yesterday...
- That difficult Cha Ju-heon...

52
00:02:50,236 --> 00:02:50,965
Boss.

53
00:02:50,990 --> 00:02:52,859
How did he change so suddenly?

54
00:02:53,117 --> 00:02:54,554
All those rules...

55
00:02:54,896 --> 00:02:56,687
Why did he make an exception for Won-young?

56
00:02:56,712 --> 00:02:59,000
Where did he go without
even leaving a note?

57
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:02,250
Boss, how can I get him to take the bait?

58
00:03:02,804 --> 00:03:04,648
I didn't realize you
cared about me this much.

59
00:03:05,796 --> 00:03:06,570
Thank you.

60
00:03:06,595 --> 00:03:09,343
But I might not deserve
to hear this from you.

61
00:03:12,490 --> 00:03:12,888
Oh?

62
00:03:12,913 --> 00:03:14,553
I once got burned by a spark.

63
00:03:14,727 --> 00:03:15,880
That must have hurt.

64
00:03:15,905 --> 00:03:17,594
No matter how you get hurt...

65
00:03:17,805 --> 00:03:19,395
A wound is still a wound.

66
00:03:19,420 --> 00:03:21,110
I know you're thinking about it...

67
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:22,805
But don't forget...

68
00:03:22,992 --> 00:03:25,453
(Hoping our hearts connect)
He's just passing through.

69
00:03:26,422 --> 00:03:28,383
Boss, do you actually
have someone you like?

70
00:03:29,094 --> 00:03:30,163
Something like this...

71
00:03:30,404 --> 00:03:33,086
Shouldn't you do it for a woman you like?

72
00:03:34,290 --> 00:03:35,620
If it were a female student...

73
00:03:35,915 --> 00:03:37,330
(Meeting and)
Her heart would definitely flutter.

74
00:03:37,354 --> 00:03:38,602
If it's a male student,

75
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:39,913
wouldn't he feel the same way?

76
00:03:39,937 --> 00:03:42,649
(Meeting and Love)

77
00:03:47,157 --> 00:03:48,110
Boss...

78
00:03:48,135 --> 00:03:49,508
I have to go find a house.

79
00:03:49,533 --> 00:03:51,119
Why is it okay for other
guys but not for me?

80
00:03:51,143 --> 00:03:52,532
You're my mom's friend's son.

81
00:03:53,622 --> 00:03:55,672
What did I just hear?

82
00:03:58,020 --> 00:03:59,405
Since it's the last night...

83
00:03:59,430 --> 00:04:01,282
I decided to buy something nice.

84
00:04:01,610 --> 00:04:03,282
Even though we couldn't drink together...

85
00:04:03,307 --> 00:04:04,532
I left it for you.

86
00:04:07,955 --> 00:04:09,399
Please stop confusing me like this.

87
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,852
I'm already overwhelmed by my own feelings.

88
00:04:12,829 --> 00:04:13,829
What feelings?

89
00:04:13,860 --> 00:04:14,920
Your feelings.

90
00:04:15,961 --> 00:04:17,141
What are they exactly?

91
00:04:18,313 --> 00:04:20,758
I'm about to do something crazy.

92
00:04:22,685 --> 00:04:23,685
I...

93
00:04:24,399 --> 00:04:26,055
I like you, Boss.

94
00:04:29,660 --> 00:04:30,735
Thank you.

95
00:04:31,102 --> 00:04:32,375
Thank you for coming to me.

96
00:04:37,790 --> 00:04:38,966
That was supposed to be my line.

97
00:04:38,990 --> 00:04:39,990
Go ahead and do it.

98
00:04:40,961 --> 00:04:42,243
Everything you want to do.

99
00:04:44,164 --> 00:04:45,410
But...

100
00:04:47,910 --> 00:04:49,257
Just don't lie to me.

101
00:04:52,554 --> 00:04:54,430
Didn't you say you had
something to tell me?

102
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,907
I'm sorry, Boss...

103
00:04:59,649 --> 00:05:01,836
How was I supposed
to know I'd fall for you?

104
00:05:04,230 --> 00:05:06,102
I only did it because I didn't know.

105
00:05:08,912 --> 00:05:09,912
This job...

106
00:05:09,937 --> 00:05:11,055
I'm quitting.

107
00:05:13,594 --> 00:05:15,250
I can't keep lying anymore.

108
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:21,844
Just wait for me a little longer.

109
00:05:22,079 --> 00:05:23,571
I'll set everything right.

110
00:05:36,860 --> 00:05:37,920
Hello.

111
00:05:38,579 --> 00:05:39,690
Oh.

112
00:05:39,930 --> 00:05:40,990
It's Won-young.

113
00:05:41,350 --> 00:05:42,282
Ah...

114
00:05:42,307 --> 00:05:43,961
Tae-jun is inside. Go on in.

115
00:05:43,986 --> 00:05:45,180
Thank you.

116
00:05:46,670 --> 00:05:47,670
No, thank you.

117
00:05:50,344 --> 00:05:51,420
That guy, Tae-jun...

118
00:05:51,445 --> 00:05:52,821
For making him smile again...

119
00:05:53,141 --> 00:05:54,141
I'm really grateful.

120
00:06:20,844 --> 00:06:22,118
Surprise!

121
00:06:24,207 --> 00:06:25,207
Oh...

122
00:06:26,944 --> 00:06:29,499
I'm here for my lover,
who was stolen by a jar.

123
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,200
Geez.

124
00:06:31,860 --> 00:06:33,719
I thought I was seeing things.

125
00:06:36,087 --> 00:06:37,087
Look!

126
00:06:37,538 --> 00:06:38,538
Hmm?

127
00:06:39,610 --> 00:06:41,460
When you get into your work...

128
00:06:41,485 --> 00:06:42,938
You forget to eat, don't you?

129
00:06:47,711 --> 00:06:49,821
Ah, I pulled an all-nighter...

130
00:06:57,297 --> 00:06:58,852
Am I bothering you?

131
00:07:22,913 --> 00:07:24,056
Not at all.

132
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,440
Wow.

133
00:07:29,610 --> 00:07:31,032
I finally feel alive again.

134
00:07:51,139 --> 00:07:52,139
That's good.

135
00:08:03,530 --> 00:08:04,530
Oh, right!

136
00:08:04,641 --> 00:08:05,921
You haven't eaten yet, have you?

137
00:08:08,305 --> 00:08:10,020
I made some spicy rice cakes...

138
00:08:10,164 --> 00:08:11,460
They're absolutely delicious.

139
00:08:11,485 --> 00:08:12,696
Really?

140
00:08:13,229 --> 00:08:14,352
Let's eat together.

141
00:08:19,113 --> 00:08:20,113
Ah...

142
00:08:20,180 --> 00:08:21,461
Right, the taxi.

143
00:08:22,806 --> 00:08:25,555
Ho-tae has to leave
for his tutoring session.

144
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:28,500
Ah...

145
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:34,520
When I'm done...

146
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:35,960
I'll head to the guesthouse.

147
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:37,700
Really?

148
00:08:37,930 --> 00:08:39,050
You promised!

149
00:08:40,359 --> 00:08:41,359
I'll be waiting.

150
00:08:44,110 --> 00:08:45,250
Be careful.

151
00:08:46,005 --> 00:08:47,227
You too, Boss.

152
00:09:07,916 --> 00:09:08,916
This is so good.

153
00:09:24,820 --> 00:09:25,820
Oh, Won-young.

154
00:09:25,977 --> 00:09:26,978
I'm at Yun Tae-jun's studio right now.

155
00:09:27,002 --> 00:09:28,002
Where are you?

156
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,400
I think you owe me...

157
00:09:38,734 --> 00:09:39,734
A proper explanation.

158
00:09:49,815 --> 00:09:51,079
This is really...

159
00:09:52,860 --> 00:09:53,860
So, actually...

160
00:09:54,430 --> 00:09:56,407
I found out Tae-jun was here...

161
00:09:56,883 --> 00:09:58,391
Through Won-young.

162
00:10:00,383 --> 00:10:02,008
What's the relationship between you two?

163
00:10:02,170 --> 00:10:03,170
Well...

164
00:10:04,227 --> 00:10:05,239
This Mr. Ji Won-young

165
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:07,760
was an employee in our General
Affairs team at Taepyeong Group.

166
00:10:08,582 --> 00:10:09,402
Although he's currently

167
00:10:09,427 --> 00:10:12,313
suspended due to a corruption case...

168
00:10:12,680 --> 00:10:14,711
Before that, the Chairman
had already given orders...

169
00:10:14,735 --> 00:10:16,586
For him to track you down, Mr. Yun.

170
00:10:19,008 --> 00:10:21,094
Meaning he already knew what I looked like.

171
00:10:22,233 --> 00:10:23,233
Exactly.

172
00:10:23,930 --> 00:10:25,338
Ah, but at that time...

173
00:10:25,363 --> 00:10:28,149
The whole industry was buzzing
trying to find you.

174
00:10:28,174 --> 00:10:30,149
And of course, our Chairman...

175
00:10:30,174 --> 00:10:33,038
You know he's not the
type to just sit back and wait.

176
00:10:33,063 --> 00:10:34,180
So...

177
00:10:37,211 --> 00:10:39,954
Ji Won-young didn't just meet me

178
00:10:43,368 --> 00:10:44,520
recently...

179
00:10:44,968 --> 00:10:45,968
Yes, that's right.

180
00:10:47,125 --> 00:10:48,220
Back then...

181
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:50,852
It was shortly after he was suspended.

182
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:52,720
Ah.

183
00:10:53,419 --> 00:10:54,985
He said he wanted to clear his head...

184
00:10:55,187 --> 00:10:56,516
So he went to Gangneung...

185
00:10:56,541 --> 00:10:58,344
And happened to stumble upon your trail.

186
00:10:58,369 --> 00:10:59,961
Then not long after...

187
00:11:00,950 --> 00:11:02,844
He contacted me and asked...

188
00:11:03,669 --> 00:11:05,199
If he could convince you

189
00:11:05,579 --> 00:11:07,750
to sign an exclusive contract with us...

190
00:11:08,407 --> 00:11:09,840
If he could get his job back.

191
00:11:47,041 --> 00:11:48,852
He contacted me and asked...

192
00:11:50,258 --> 00:11:51,930
that if he could convince you

193
00:11:52,071 --> 00:11:53,836
to sign an exclusive contract with us...

194
00:11:54,774 --> 00:11:56,141
would it be possible to
could get his job back.

195
00:12:19,399 --> 00:12:21,422
It's getting late...

196
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:24,743
Ah, I forgot to bring my phone back...

197
00:12:27,126 --> 00:12:28,230
Who is it?

198
00:12:29,095 --> 00:12:30,095
It's me.

199
00:12:30,937 --> 00:12:31,937
Boss?

200
00:12:37,790 --> 00:12:39,830
I guess you came up
because I didn't have my phone.

201
00:12:40,313 --> 00:12:41,420
Anyway, please come in.

202
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:58,532
Ah...

203
00:12:58,557 --> 00:12:59,766
The place is a mess, isn't it?

204
00:13:05,079 --> 00:13:06,210
Boss.

205
00:13:18,842 --> 00:13:19,802
I finally got my phone back...

206
00:13:19,834 --> 00:13:21,119
Not having it for just a little while...

207
00:13:21,143 --> 00:13:22,305
Was so inconvenient.

208
00:13:22,330 --> 00:13:23,850
I couldn't even get in touch with you.

209
00:13:28,567 --> 00:13:29,797
Are you looking for a job?

210
00:13:31,140 --> 00:13:32,310
Ah, yes.

211
00:13:32,905 --> 00:13:35,705
I'm looking at companies with
openings in the first half of next year.

212
00:13:38,055 --> 00:13:39,579
Not interested in Taepyeong?

213
00:13:42,625 --> 00:13:44,102
That's a big company too.

214
00:13:46,370 --> 00:13:47,370
Oh...

215
00:13:48,223 --> 00:13:50,533
They don't seem to have any openings.

216
00:13:51,860 --> 00:13:53,260
I'm not sure about the second half.

217
00:13:53,419 --> 00:13:55,375
Actually, I have some connections there.

218
00:13:55,596 --> 00:13:56,836
At the Taepyeong Gallery.

219
00:13:57,963 --> 00:14:00,003
I even have my own
dedicated exhibition hall there.

220
00:14:01,374 --> 00:14:02,374
What do you think?

221
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:05,735
Through the people I know,

222
00:14:07,214 --> 00:14:08,650
I could ask them to get you a job.

223
00:14:11,274 --> 00:14:12,470
Want me to try?

224
00:14:13,050 --> 00:14:14,050
No, thank you.

225
00:14:14,134 --> 00:14:14,859
This is my career.

226
00:14:14,891 --> 00:14:16,021
I should do it on my own.

227
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,320
Is that so?

228
00:14:25,055 --> 00:14:26,219
Won-young.

229
00:14:26,860 --> 00:14:27,961
On your own...

230
00:14:32,009 --> 00:14:33,009
I'm leaving.

231
00:14:34,905 --> 00:14:36,305
You're leaving just like that?

232
00:14:38,473 --> 00:14:39,696
Boss.

233
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:42,579
Is everything okay?

234
00:14:43,990 --> 00:14:44,990
Get some rest.

235
00:15:00,266 --> 00:15:01,867
Can't you stay a bit longer...

236
00:15:06,630 --> 00:15:07,355
Boss...

237
00:15:07,380 --> 00:15:09,032
Manager Jeong told me everything.

238
00:15:09,665 --> 00:15:12,297
About why you've been staying by my side.

239
00:15:13,554 --> 00:15:14,790
I don't know how he found out,

240
00:15:15,922 --> 00:15:17,415
but he came straight to my studio.

241
00:15:18,340 --> 00:15:20,260
How long were you
planning to keep this from me?

242
00:15:20,290 --> 00:15:21,875
- Boss...
- I was thinking...

243
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:24,321
If you were honest with me now,

244
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:26,477
I would reconsider.

245
00:15:26,790 --> 00:15:28,782
Maybe you had a reason
you couldn't tell me?

246
00:15:30,110 --> 00:15:32,540
You were so upset that day in Seoul.

247
00:15:32,565 --> 00:15:34,915
I wondered if it was because of this.

248
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:36,770
But in the end,

249
00:15:38,797 --> 00:15:40,149
you still chose the company.

250
00:15:41,974 --> 00:15:42,974
Back then,

251
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:44,970
and even now.

252
00:15:44,971 --> 00:15:46,000
No.

253
00:15:46,571 --> 00:15:47,740
That's not it.

254
00:15:49,196 --> 00:15:50,860
I was just scared.

255
00:15:51,336 --> 00:15:53,976
I was afraid that if I told you everything,
you'd break up with me.

256
00:15:54,336 --> 00:15:55,950
I was terrified of losing you.

257
00:15:56,362 --> 00:15:57,362
Yeah, of course.

258
00:15:58,353 --> 00:15:59,133
Because if we break up,

259
00:15:59,158 --> 00:16:00,416
your whole plan goes down the drain.

260
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:01,210
What are you saying...

261
00:16:01,235 --> 00:16:02,829
Did you think it was the perfect chance

262
00:16:03,081 --> 00:16:04,082
since I fell for you faster than expected?

263
00:16:04,106 --> 00:16:05,106
I didn't.

264
00:16:05,131 --> 00:16:06,430
I never thought that.

265
00:16:06,455 --> 00:16:07,325
Another lie.

266
00:16:07,350 --> 00:16:08,493
I'm not lying.

267
00:16:08,518 --> 00:16:10,750
- I really...
- You expect me to believe that?

268
00:16:12,188 --> 00:16:12,969
Boss.

269
00:16:12,994 --> 00:16:13,994
Now,

270
00:16:16,438 --> 00:16:17,993
where your plan ends

271
00:16:20,211 --> 00:16:21,993
and where your true feelings begin...

272
00:16:24,381 --> 00:16:25,508
I can't tell anymore.

273
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:53,390
Boss.

274
00:16:54,785 --> 00:16:55,969
Mr. Ji Won-young.

275
00:17:03,890 --> 00:17:05,461
Let's not see each other anymore.

276
00:18:42,810 --> 00:18:43,810
What are you doing?

277
00:18:45,150 --> 00:18:46,423
Ah, hyung.

278
00:18:47,806 --> 00:18:49,069
You're not a part-timer here.

279
00:18:49,070 --> 00:18:50,548
You're a part-timer at our shop.

280
00:18:51,425 --> 00:18:52,345
If you're coming to work,

281
00:18:52,370 --> 00:18:54,126
you should say hi to me first.

282
00:18:57,087 --> 00:19:00,424
(Closed for personal
reasons - Moon Jar Pottery)

283
00:19:01,430 --> 00:19:02,430
What's wrong?

284
00:19:02,579 --> 00:19:03,704
Why do you look so terrible?

285
00:19:03,729 --> 00:19:04,729
Boss.

286
00:19:05,126 --> 00:19:06,295
Did he say he's not coming?

287
00:19:06,940 --> 00:19:08,384
Why are you asking me?

288
00:19:10,482 --> 00:19:12,853
I got a message saying
he'd be out for a few days.

289
00:19:14,282 --> 00:19:17,314
I guess when you own the
place, you do what you want.

290
00:19:18,604 --> 00:19:19,716
Is it because he was
born with a silver spoon?

291
00:19:19,740 --> 00:19:20,740
Hyung.

292
00:19:21,059 --> 00:19:22,059
Today,

293
00:19:22,377 --> 00:19:24,111
can I leave early?

294
00:19:25,572 --> 00:19:26,447
Yeah.

295
00:19:26,472 --> 00:19:27,472
Sure.

296
00:19:27,877 --> 00:19:28,990
Thank you.

297
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:36,920
Boss.

298
00:20:37,119 --> 00:20:38,210
Boss!

299
00:20:38,791 --> 00:20:39,910
Boss!

300
00:20:54,506 --> 00:20:57,138
(For Won-young)

301
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:00,910
I made a lamp.

302
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:02,560
A lamp?

303
00:21:03,855 --> 00:21:05,015
But I'm not giving it to you.

304
00:21:05,343 --> 00:21:05,803
Why not?

305
00:21:05,828 --> 00:21:07,708
I'm going to keep it in
the room you stayed in.

306
00:21:08,243 --> 00:21:09,243
If you want to see it,

307
00:21:09,769 --> 00:21:10,769
you'll have to come back.

308
00:21:29,037 --> 00:21:34,357
(For Won-young)

309
00:22:16,537 --> 00:22:18,373
That guy finally showed up for work.

310
00:22:22,326 --> 00:22:23,030
Wow...

311
00:22:23,055 --> 00:22:24,912
He skipped work for three days.

312
00:22:25,323 --> 00:22:27,482
Hyung, excuse me for a second.

313
00:22:39,414 --> 00:22:40,414
Boss.

314
00:22:40,482 --> 00:22:41,482
Do you not understand

315
00:22:41,641 --> 00:22:42,861
what I said?

316
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:45,724
I told you not to see me anymore.

317
00:22:45,749 --> 00:22:47,427
Please, just listen to me once.

318
00:22:51,607 --> 00:22:53,138
It's all my fault.

319
00:22:53,831 --> 00:22:56,295
I did approach you on purpose.

320
00:22:56,445 --> 00:22:58,912
And it's my fault for
not telling you sooner.

321
00:22:59,775 --> 00:23:01,655
I really shouldn't have done that.

322
00:23:02,883 --> 00:23:04,693
I know it sounds like an excuse,

323
00:23:04,718 --> 00:23:06,545
but your kindness...

324
00:23:07,157 --> 00:23:09,068
I never once saw it as just an opportunity.

325
00:23:10,334 --> 00:23:12,123
Falling for you

326
00:23:13,497 --> 00:23:15,295
was never part of the plan.

327
00:23:17,193 --> 00:23:19,753
- This is how I really feel...
- You're quite greedy, aren't you?

328
00:23:27,969 --> 00:23:30,231
I guess you realized you can't
go back to the company right away.

329
00:23:30,255 --> 00:23:32,740
So you're staying by my
side, waiting for the right time.

330
00:23:34,605 --> 00:23:35,605
Are you

331
00:23:37,146 --> 00:23:38,340
changing your strategy?

332
00:23:38,365 --> 00:23:40,013
- Boss...
- Stop acting.

333
00:23:42,138 --> 00:23:43,258
I'll give you what you want.

334
00:23:44,130 --> 00:23:45,330
I'll make your wish come true.

335
00:23:45,654 --> 00:23:46,810
What does that mean?

336
00:23:58,382 --> 00:23:59,382
Answer it.

337
00:24:01,451 --> 00:24:02,730
It looks like Manager Jeong.

338
00:24:09,830 --> 00:24:10,530
Hello?

339
00:24:10,755 --> 00:24:11,412
Won-young?

340
00:24:11,437 --> 00:24:11,930
Ah, well...

341
00:24:11,931 --> 00:24:13,100
You haven't heard from
General Affairs yet, have you?

342
00:24:13,124 --> 00:24:14,740
Man, this is great news.

343
00:24:14,765 --> 00:24:17,224
Won-young, you can come back
to work the day after tomorrow.

344
00:24:17,555 --> 00:24:18,555
That artist, Yun Tae-jun,

345
00:24:18,923 --> 00:24:20,883
he decided to sign an
exclusive contract with us.

346
00:24:21,549 --> 00:24:23,263
Wow... this is all thanks
to you, Won-young.

347
00:24:23,287 --> 00:24:23,810
Did you know?

348
00:24:24,044 --> 00:24:25,123
Tae-jun

349
00:24:25,148 --> 00:24:26,990
specifically asked for
you to be reinstated.

350
00:24:27,124 --> 00:24:28,324
He made a special point of it.

351
00:24:30,413 --> 00:24:31,413
Boss.

352
00:24:31,651 --> 00:24:33,552
- What I want is...
- Go back to work.

353
00:24:35,260 --> 00:24:37,263
This is the last bit of
mercy I'll show you.

354
00:24:38,795 --> 00:24:39,995
And it's also your punishment.

355
00:24:41,635 --> 00:24:42,885
I want you,

356
00:24:43,930 --> 00:24:46,084
Ji Won-young, to live with the guilt.

357
00:25:09,587 --> 00:25:10,788
Do you want to get
beaten up before you leave?

358
00:25:10,812 --> 00:25:12,005
Or are you going to leave quietly?

359
00:25:12,029 --> 00:25:13,740
If you agree to date me for a month,

360
00:25:14,262 --> 00:25:15,396
I'll leave right now.

361
00:25:21,715 --> 00:25:23,005
I told you to get out.

362
00:25:23,187 --> 00:25:24,763
Sigh... rejected again.

363
00:25:25,194 --> 00:25:26,274
How many times is that now?

364
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:42,513
Hey, what's wrong with you?

365
00:25:49,620 --> 00:25:50,620
Are you

366
00:25:50,645 --> 00:25:51,645
okay?

367
00:25:52,837 --> 00:25:53,837
Yeah.

368
00:25:55,010 --> 00:25:55,680
What happened?

369
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:56,680
Part-timer.

370
00:25:58,055 --> 00:25:59,055
You two...

371
00:26:00,115 --> 00:26:01,259
Did you guys get into a fight?

372
00:26:01,260 --> 00:26:03,224
Won-young, what's wrong?

373
00:26:04,308 --> 00:26:05,920
Cha Ju-heon did this, didn't he?

374
00:26:10,410 --> 00:26:11,427
Seriously.

375
00:26:12,101 --> 00:26:13,396
What did he say to you?

376
00:26:15,461 --> 00:26:17,748
No, really, what did he say to this kid?

377
00:26:18,758 --> 00:26:19,758
This can't go on.

378
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:24,000
No, it's not that.

379
00:26:24,334 --> 00:26:25,638
I was wrong.

380
00:26:25,896 --> 00:26:27,451
I lied.

381
00:26:52,770 --> 00:26:54,638
(Did the Boss come to the shop today?)

382
00:26:54,663 --> 00:26:56,271
(Did the Boss eat well?)

383
00:26:56,350 --> 00:26:57,920
(Is the Boss doing okay?)

384
00:27:04,010 --> 00:27:05,010
Hello?

385
00:27:06,330 --> 00:27:07,755
Is this the soup restaurant?

386
00:27:09,130 --> 00:27:10,951
Two iced Americanos.

387
00:27:11,155 --> 00:27:12,529
And two lattes?

388
00:27:13,560 --> 00:27:14,779
Okay, I got it.

389
00:27:24,779 --> 00:27:26,357
Fruit delivery complete.

390
00:27:27,091 --> 00:27:28,271
Whoa.

391
00:27:28,570 --> 00:27:29,755
You scared me.

392
00:27:31,429 --> 00:27:33,869
The coffee beans will be here
soon, so make sure to get them.

393
00:27:38,818 --> 00:27:40,201
Just date me for a month.

394
00:27:52,937 --> 00:27:54,146
Still not leaving?

395
00:28:05,472 --> 00:28:06,472
I'm leaving.

396
00:28:08,963 --> 00:28:10,826
The Earth is spinning.

397
00:28:11,125 --> 00:28:12,380
Are you losing your mind too?

398
00:28:15,862 --> 00:28:16,862
I'm spinning.

399
00:28:17,891 --> 00:28:19,331
You look much better when you smile.

400
00:28:24,115 --> 00:28:25,600
I've been watching you.

401
00:28:26,067 --> 00:28:28,013
You get angry because of me,

402
00:28:28,517 --> 00:28:29,920
and you smile because of me.

403
00:28:30,460 --> 00:28:32,005
Yet you say you're not interested.

404
00:28:38,716 --> 00:28:39,780
Hey, driver.

405
00:28:40,205 --> 00:28:41,701
I'll go get the coffee beans.

406
00:29:06,552 --> 00:29:07,888
One cinnamon latte.

407
00:29:22,021 --> 00:29:23,380
I guess you're still angry.

408
00:29:23,478 --> 00:29:25,693
Oh, Mr. Yun Tae-jun.

409
00:29:25,773 --> 00:29:27,880
What right do I have to be angry?

410
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:30,396
My back still hurts

411
00:29:30,421 --> 00:29:33,334
from being stabbed by a trusted friend.

412
00:29:33,359 --> 00:29:34,795
I told you I had my reasons.

413
00:29:35,560 --> 00:29:37,099
- I'm sorry.
- Then Won-young...

414
00:29:37,826 --> 00:29:39,386
Don't you think he had his reasons too?

415
00:29:40,421 --> 00:29:42,221
I heard he already
submitted his resignation.

416
00:29:42,278 --> 00:29:44,302
Wait, a guy who wanted his job back

417
00:29:44,505 --> 00:29:46,025
would have to be crazy to quit, right?

418
00:29:46,552 --> 00:29:48,192
If you're not making
me coffee, I'm leaving.

419
00:29:48,216 --> 00:29:49,193
Fine, go ahead. Leave.

420
00:29:49,218 --> 00:29:50,218
You're so stubborn.

421
00:29:51,342 --> 00:29:52,342
I'm leaving then.

422
00:29:53,865 --> 00:29:54,960
Hey, hey, hey.

423
00:29:55,693 --> 00:29:57,293
I tell you to leave and you actually do?

424
00:29:58,220 --> 00:29:59,220
Wait a second.

425
00:30:02,201 --> 00:30:03,849
I think he's being sincere.

426
00:30:04,482 --> 00:30:06,052
I can tell just by looking at his face.

427
00:30:06,521 --> 00:30:08,084
Why do you refuse to see it?

428
00:30:14,466 --> 00:30:16,209
If this were the first time,

429
00:30:18,052 --> 00:30:19,591
maybe I'd try to believe him.

430
00:30:21,317 --> 00:30:23,396
But even after five
years, things can fall apart.

431
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:25,480
That's what trust is.

432
00:30:29,037 --> 00:30:30,437
And we've only known each other for

433
00:30:30,693 --> 00:30:31,904
two or three months.

434
00:30:32,662 --> 00:30:33,750
Tae-jun.

435
00:30:35,430 --> 00:30:37,357
Do you think I'd still be valuable to you

436
00:30:39,462 --> 00:30:41,740
without your father's influence?

437
00:30:48,263 --> 00:30:49,670
These belong to Won-young.

438
00:30:51,345 --> 00:30:52,545
It seems he's not coming back.

439
00:30:52,780 --> 00:30:54,412
Should I clear them away?

440
00:30:59,982 --> 00:31:01,010
Just leave them.

441
00:31:01,388 --> 00:31:02,530
I'll take care of it.

442
00:31:02,610 --> 00:31:04,162
I'll leave them here then.

443
00:31:08,080 --> 00:31:09,350
Good work today.

444
00:31:09,660 --> 00:31:10,966
See you tomorrow.

445
00:31:13,013 --> 00:31:14,230
Good work.

446
00:31:23,179 --> 00:31:24,179
Sir.

447
00:31:24,552 --> 00:31:25,912
Could you take a look at mine too?

448
00:31:26,496 --> 00:31:27,740
I'm not sure how to use this.

449
00:31:27,869 --> 00:31:28,869
Ji Won-young.

450
00:31:29,763 --> 00:31:32,280
What am I going to do if
you can't even do the basics?

451
00:31:32,305 --> 00:31:33,490
How many classes has it been?

452
00:31:39,790 --> 00:31:41,748
Seriously, you're teasing
me again, aren't you?

453
00:31:46,404 --> 00:31:47,480
I'm done.

454
00:31:54,910 --> 00:31:55,910
<i>Hey.</i>

455
00:31:56,936 --> 00:31:57,936
What's going on?

456
00:31:58,208 --> 00:32:00,537
You sound like a total wreck.

457
00:32:01,372 --> 00:32:02,372
<i>Dong-hee hyung?</i>

458
00:32:03,521 --> 00:32:04,150
Yeah, it's me.

459
00:32:04,465 --> 00:32:05,834
I'm outside your place.

460
00:32:06,015 --> 00:32:07,015
<i>You're at my place?</i>

461
00:32:07,206 --> 00:32:07,946
Yeah.

462
00:32:08,215 --> 00:32:09,215
Come on out!

463
00:32:10,012 --> 00:32:11,132
This is a nice neighborhood.

464
00:32:14,318 --> 00:32:15,400
You're not...

465
00:32:15,826 --> 00:32:17,787
secretly rich, are you?

466
00:32:18,776 --> 00:32:19,776
No way.

467
00:32:22,212 --> 00:32:23,457
I don't believe you.

468
00:32:23,670 --> 00:32:25,084
It's hard to believe.

469
00:32:31,030 --> 00:32:32,030
Aren't you drinking?

470
00:32:33,590 --> 00:32:34,590
No.

471
00:32:37,715 --> 00:32:39,623
Shouldn't you be at the
cafe? Why are you here?

472
00:32:40,396 --> 00:32:41,818
I left Ho-tae in charge.

473
00:32:41,880 --> 00:32:43,160
He even does the deliveries now.

474
00:32:43,490 --> 00:32:44,490
Man.

475
00:32:45,930 --> 00:32:48,552
I promised to stay until
Ho-tae passed his exam.

476
00:32:49,433 --> 00:32:50,433
I'm really sorry.

477
00:32:50,458 --> 00:32:51,371
Geez.

478
00:32:51,396 --> 00:32:52,516
You have a lot more to apologize for

479
00:32:52,540 --> 00:32:53,857
than just that.

480
00:32:56,567 --> 00:32:57,567
But anyway,

481
00:32:58,120 --> 00:32:59,795
I don't know what got into him,

482
00:33:00,164 --> 00:33:02,396
but he seems to be taking
it more seriously now.

483
00:33:02,576 --> 00:33:04,318
He's the type who does what he says.

484
00:33:06,010 --> 00:33:07,010
That's good to hear.

485
00:33:07,976 --> 00:33:08,976
Ju-heon...

486
00:33:10,170 --> 00:33:11,302
Wait, no...

487
00:33:12,373 --> 00:33:13,865
Tae-jun's shop...

488
00:33:15,593 --> 00:33:17,833
People are coming all the
way from Seoul just to see it.

489
00:33:19,075 --> 00:33:21,927
It really hit me that he's famous.

490
00:33:22,113 --> 00:33:23,998
But it's also kind of annoying to watch.

491
00:33:29,260 --> 00:33:30,260
Are you

492
00:33:31,220 --> 00:33:32,220
eating properly?

493
00:33:32,245 --> 00:33:33,670
Yes, I've been eating well.

494
00:33:34,249 --> 00:33:36,427
Look at you, lying again.

495
00:33:37,224 --> 00:33:38,474
Just look at yourself.

496
00:33:38,666 --> 00:33:40,927
You look like you're about to waste away.

497
00:33:47,028 --> 00:33:48,028
What about the company?

498
00:33:50,451 --> 00:33:52,584
It's been almost a week since you went in.

499
00:33:52,708 --> 00:33:54,468
Are they just going
to wait for you forever?

500
00:33:54,654 --> 00:33:56,451
If I go back to work,

501
00:33:58,072 --> 00:33:59,792
doesn't that mean I'm okay with everything?

502
00:34:01,193 --> 00:34:03,412
Then I really would be the kind of person

503
00:34:04,490 --> 00:34:06,638
who betrayed the Boss
just to get his job back.

504
00:34:10,757 --> 00:34:11,757
But...

505
00:34:15,482 --> 00:34:16,620
I really...

506
00:34:17,185 --> 00:34:18,646
miss him so much...

507
00:34:22,295 --> 00:34:23,440
Just go back to work.

508
00:34:25,673 --> 00:34:27,654
Didn't you say this chance came

509
00:34:28,466 --> 00:34:30,106
because of the contract with Yun Tae-jun?

510
00:34:31,114 --> 00:34:32,754
Are you just going to let it go to waste?

511
00:34:32,943 --> 00:34:34,216
You're all in the same group, right?

512
00:34:34,240 --> 00:34:35,240
Maybe...

513
00:34:35,623 --> 00:34:36,958
you'll even run into him!

514
00:35:16,826 --> 00:35:18,975
(Guys, don't make it so obvious.)

515
00:35:19,513 --> 00:35:21,248
(Nothing's been confirmed yet!)

516
00:35:21,480 --> 00:35:23,951
(How did this connection suddenly appear
when it wasn't there before?)

517
00:35:23,975 --> 00:35:24,638
(Exactly.)

518
00:35:24,663 --> 00:35:26,730
(And how do they explain
his sudden reinstatement?)

519
00:35:26,755 --> 00:35:27,440
(Right!)

520
00:35:27,441 --> 00:35:29,536
(The internal investigation on
Manager Kim isn't even over.)

521
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:31,440
(It's suspicious no
matter how you look at it.)

522
00:35:31,540 --> 00:35:33,714
Alright, Won-young is back.

523
00:35:34,730 --> 00:35:36,400
Won-young, you can sit here.

524
00:35:37,375 --> 00:35:38,375
Let's work hard together.

525
00:35:49,570 --> 00:35:51,034
Oh, Won-young, you're here?

526
00:35:52,002 --> 00:35:53,522
Congratulations on your reinstatement.

527
00:35:54,550 --> 00:35:55,550
Where are you going?

528
00:35:55,575 --> 00:35:57,011
I need about two people

529
00:35:57,503 --> 00:35:58,220
who can work overtime today.

530
00:35:58,310 --> 00:35:59,460
What's the task?

531
00:36:00,420 --> 00:36:02,285
Come on.

532
00:36:02,310 --> 00:36:04,465
It's Friday night, Team Leader!

533
00:36:04,490 --> 00:36:07,206
It's an urgent request from the gallery.

534
00:36:08,710 --> 00:36:09,581
Team Leader,

535
00:36:09,730 --> 00:36:10,814
what's going on over there?

536
00:36:10,839 --> 00:36:12,769
You know that new potter we signed?

537
00:36:12,794 --> 00:36:14,381
They need to shoot his portfolio.

538
00:36:14,406 --> 00:36:16,292
The production team is short-handed.

539
00:36:16,675 --> 00:36:18,190
It's the Chairman's favorite.

540
00:36:20,170 --> 00:36:21,644
Is it Yun Tae-jun?

541
00:36:23,450 --> 00:36:24,855
I'll go!

542
00:36:25,890 --> 00:36:26,890
Me too!

543
00:36:46,597 --> 00:36:48,045
Artist, you're here?

544
00:36:48,070 --> 00:36:49,698
Hello! Hello!

545
00:36:51,401 --> 00:36:52,644
Tae-jun is here.

546
00:36:59,063 --> 00:37:01,230
Don't look. Let's just finish up quickly.

547
00:37:01,558 --> 00:37:03,438
I'll be right back. I need
to use the restroom.

548
00:37:42,935 --> 00:37:44,857
The support from headquarters...

549
00:37:45,372 --> 00:37:46,638
turned out to be Won-young.

550
00:37:48,720 --> 00:37:50,833
This contract was all thanks to you.

551
00:37:51,510 --> 00:37:53,490
And yet, here you are
doing this kind of work.

552
00:37:53,973 --> 00:37:55,411
It breaks my heart to see it.

553
00:37:55,436 --> 00:37:56,436
Did you...

554
00:37:56,610 --> 00:37:58,660
say hello to Tae-jun yet?

555
00:37:58,685 --> 00:38:00,606
You promised you wouldn't tell him first.

556
00:38:00,732 --> 00:38:02,504
I was surprised too.

557
00:38:02,958 --> 00:38:04,410
I was trying to keep my promise,

558
00:38:04,477 --> 00:38:06,340
so I called you first.

559
00:38:07,291 --> 00:38:09,192
How was I supposed to
know he'd answer your phone?

560
00:38:09,216 --> 00:38:10,794
But going all the way there...

561
00:38:10,826 --> 00:38:12,856
Well, the result was good, wasn't it?

562
00:38:12,964 --> 00:38:15,098
We got the contract with Tae-jun,

563
00:38:15,210 --> 00:38:16,420
and you got your job back.

564
00:38:16,491 --> 00:38:17,491
And besides,

565
00:38:17,684 --> 00:38:20,403
relationships have their ups and downs.

566
00:38:20,864 --> 00:38:22,130
Just be patient.

567
00:38:22,648 --> 00:38:23,648
Later on,

568
00:38:23,673 --> 00:38:25,747
I'll find a chance to talk to him for you.

569
00:38:27,501 --> 00:38:28,512
Good work.

570
00:38:34,637 --> 00:38:35,833
Hello, Mr. Yun.

571
00:38:36,440 --> 00:38:37,440
Hello.

572
00:38:37,544 --> 00:38:38,544
Wow, this

573
00:38:38,957 --> 00:38:40,286
piece is absolutely stunning.

574
00:38:42,387 --> 00:38:43,942
I'll leave the photography to you.

575
00:38:45,133 --> 00:38:46,497
Who else can I blame?

576
00:38:48,286 --> 00:38:49,481
It's all my fault.

577
00:39:11,007 --> 00:39:12,043
For today's shoot,

578
00:39:12,114 --> 00:39:13,460
is there anyone else besides Mr. Yun?

579
00:39:13,461 --> 00:39:14,481
Yeah, I think so.

580
00:39:15,161 --> 00:39:16,520
An artist named Choi In-ho.

581
00:39:16,965 --> 00:39:18,400
Manager Park, I'm sorry.

582
00:39:18,425 --> 00:39:19,535
I'm really sorry.

583
00:39:19,825 --> 00:39:20,825
Won-young!

584
00:39:21,122 --> 00:39:22,122
Where are you going?

585
00:39:22,481 --> 00:39:23,835
Mr. Choi, you're here.

586
00:39:23,860 --> 00:39:24,981
You look busy today.

587
00:39:25,006 --> 00:39:26,346
Because Mr. Yun is here too.

588
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:27,145
Is he inside?

589
00:39:27,170 --> 00:39:29,380
Yes, he should be in the lounge.

590
00:39:39,102 --> 00:39:40,125
(Hwang Su-min)

591
00:39:41,095 --> 00:39:42,196
(Yun Tae-jun)

592
00:40:09,329 --> 00:40:10,329
Tae-jun.

593
00:40:14,821 --> 00:40:15,821
What...

594
00:40:17,923 --> 00:40:18,923
He's not here.

595
00:40:33,688 --> 00:40:34,735
Excuse me...

596
00:40:35,734 --> 00:40:38,392
I'm enough of a headache for him as it is.

597
00:40:58,274 --> 00:40:59,274
Come in.

598
00:41:20,696 --> 00:41:21,696
Boss.

599
00:41:23,001 --> 00:41:24,337
I'm here to help out.

600
00:41:24,362 --> 00:41:26,376
I came because I heard you'd be here.

601
00:41:27,470 --> 00:41:28,130
Just leave.

602
00:41:28,155 --> 00:41:29,155
Wait a second!

603
00:41:29,602 --> 00:41:30,750
Let's talk.

604
00:41:30,870 --> 00:41:31,870
Just for a moment.

605
00:41:44,360 --> 00:41:45,360
I

606
00:41:46,305 --> 00:41:48,508
Am accepting the punishment you gave me.

607
00:41:49,661 --> 00:41:52,001
I thought about not coming
back to the company,

608
00:41:52,867 --> 00:41:54,829
but then I thought I'd never see you again.

609
00:41:55,321 --> 00:41:57,110
I'll work really hard.

610
00:41:57,508 --> 00:41:59,334
Until you can forgive me.

611
00:41:59,359 --> 00:42:00,602
Whether you work hard or not,

612
00:42:00,891 --> 00:42:01,923
don't waste your time.

613
00:42:04,017 --> 00:42:06,537
Forgiveness is only possible
when there are still feelings left.

614
00:42:08,589 --> 00:42:10,119
But for you, Won-young,

615
00:42:10,850 --> 00:42:12,532
I don't have any feelings left.

616
00:42:14,037 --> 00:42:16,173
I'd be lying if I said I wasn't angry.

617
00:42:16,947 --> 00:42:18,829
But I've decided to try and understand.

618
00:42:19,721 --> 00:42:21,161
And I'm doing that now.

619
00:42:25,970 --> 00:42:27,110
Even now, I'm wondering...

620
00:42:29,300 --> 00:42:32,090
Why does he look so regretful?

621
00:42:32,370 --> 00:42:34,399
Is there something else

622
00:42:35,735 --> 00:42:37,516
he can use me for?

623
00:42:41,360 --> 00:42:43,016
But I'm trying to understand.

624
00:42:48,438 --> 00:42:49,438
Now, please leave.

625
00:42:50,157 --> 00:42:51,204
I need to rest.

626
00:44:00,010 --> 00:44:01,550
No matter how much I think about it,

627
00:44:02,438 --> 00:44:03,930
it's just so unfair...

628
00:44:08,884 --> 00:44:09,883
(Search: Pottery Class)

629
00:44:09,908 --> 00:44:11,025
(This is the pottery class group.
(We're meeting this Saturday.)

630
00:44:11,049 --> 00:44:12,306
(You must attend tomorrow's dinner
to complete the course.)

631
00:44:12,330 --> 00:44:13,806
(What should we get the teacher? He even
set up an exhibition for us... A scarf?)

632
00:44:13,830 --> 00:44:18,590
(No, he already has one he always wears! Let's get something
else.) (Ma'am, will the teacher be at the dinner tomorrow?)

633
00:44:20,134 --> 00:44:20,818
Right?

634
00:44:20,843 --> 00:44:22,124
Yeah.

635
00:44:22,702 --> 00:44:25,045
I'm so glad you could make it, Won-young.

636
00:44:25,070 --> 00:44:26,710
I'm sorry I left without saying goodbye.

637
00:44:26,760 --> 00:44:29,200
Oh, you got a job at a big company.

638
00:44:29,210 --> 00:44:30,361
What's there to be sorry about?

639
00:44:30,385 --> 00:44:31,585
I'm just happy for you.

640
00:44:34,170 --> 00:44:35,615
Oh! Teacher.

641
00:44:35,640 --> 00:44:36,733
Look, it's the teacher!

642
00:44:36,920 --> 00:44:37,920
He's here!

643
00:44:38,170 --> 00:44:39,248
He's here!

644
00:44:39,576 --> 00:44:40,760
Welcome.

645
00:44:46,589 --> 00:44:47,948
What are you doing?

646
00:44:48,058 --> 00:44:49,378
I know this is crazy,

647
00:44:49,403 --> 00:44:51,417
but I felt like this was
the only way to see you.

648
00:44:51,442 --> 00:44:52,925
You're exhausting.

649
00:44:56,026 --> 00:44:57,456
Didn't I say it's over?

650
00:44:57,722 --> 00:44:58,880
Do you not understand me?

651
00:44:58,905 --> 00:45:01,214
The way you just jumped to conclusions...

652
00:45:01,877 --> 00:45:03,957
The more I think about
it, the more unfair it feels.

653
00:45:04,459 --> 00:45:05,615
I jumped to conclusions?

654
00:45:05,640 --> 00:45:07,011
Even if we're really over,

655
00:45:08,229 --> 00:45:10,069
I want to clear up the
misunderstanding first.

656
00:45:10,691 --> 00:45:13,300
If you're angry because I lied to you,

657
00:45:13,448 --> 00:45:15,253
fine, I'll accept that.

658
00:45:15,278 --> 00:45:16,278
But

659
00:45:16,487 --> 00:45:18,909
if you're angry because you think

660
00:45:19,285 --> 00:45:21,095
I was faking my feelings for you,

661
00:45:24,149 --> 00:45:25,518
if that's why you can't forgive me,

662
00:45:25,542 --> 00:45:26,710
then that's just not fair.

663
00:45:27,747 --> 00:45:28,901
I'll do anything

664
00:45:28,926 --> 00:45:30,836
to prove my feelings were real.

665
00:45:30,861 --> 00:45:31,946
I'll get on my knees if I have to.

666
00:45:31,970 --> 00:45:33,222
I'll beg for your forgiveness.

667
00:45:33,331 --> 00:45:34,356
If that's what it takes for you to see,

668
00:45:34,380 --> 00:45:35,380
I'll do it.

669
00:45:36,681 --> 00:45:37,681
Why...

670
00:45:38,019 --> 00:45:40,612
Why do I have to know how you feel?

671
00:45:42,909 --> 00:45:44,651
Because it's the truth.

672
00:45:46,822 --> 00:45:48,342
I know I messed up.

673
00:45:48,545 --> 00:45:49,941
But even so,

674
00:45:51,609 --> 00:45:54,089
you don't have the right to just
assume my feelings were fake.

675
00:45:54,974 --> 00:45:56,237
It's not fair.

676
00:46:03,110 --> 00:46:04,110
Please don't run away.

677
00:46:04,111 --> 00:46:05,511
Stop assuming you know how I feel.

678
00:46:23,232 --> 00:46:24,232
Boss.

679
00:46:28,483 --> 00:46:29,739
I'll leave.

680
00:46:31,071 --> 00:46:33,075
This party is for you, after all.

681
00:47:03,670 --> 00:47:04,670
Teacher.

682
00:47:06,528 --> 00:47:07,998
Wait, where did Won-young go?

683
00:47:08,719 --> 00:47:10,434
I brought this out because it's cold.

684
00:47:11,890 --> 00:47:12,890
Where did he go?

685
00:47:13,282 --> 00:47:14,282
Hmm?

686
00:48:06,989 --> 00:48:08,903
Someone asked me to give this to you.

687
00:48:10,364 --> 00:48:11,364
Thank you.

688
00:48:27,817 --> 00:48:28,817
Boss.

689
00:48:30,347 --> 00:48:31,614
You don't have to turn around.

690
00:48:32,115 --> 00:48:33,348
Just listen.

691
00:48:34,928 --> 00:48:36,348
I'll find a way.

692
00:48:36,582 --> 00:48:38,004
I'll think harder and harder.

693
00:48:38,491 --> 00:48:39,840
I'll figure out what I need to do

694
00:48:40,629 --> 00:48:41,700
to make you believe me.

695
00:48:42,543 --> 00:48:44,090
I'll find a way.

696
00:48:44,356 --> 00:48:45,500
I'll think harder.

697
00:48:45,772 --> 00:48:47,733
I'll figure out how to make you believe me.

698
00:48:49,756 --> 00:48:51,537
I can't give up on you.

699
00:48:51,713 --> 00:48:53,131
I just can't.

700
00:49:15,130 --> 00:49:15,692
Manager Park.

701
00:49:15,717 --> 00:49:17,726
What's the plan for the internal
training courses next quarter?

702
00:49:17,750 --> 00:49:20,131
There aren't many changes overall.

703
00:49:24,029 --> 00:49:25,029
But Won-young

704
00:49:25,568 --> 00:49:27,240
has a proposal to present.

705
00:49:30,880 --> 00:49:32,040
Yes.

706
00:49:38,150 --> 00:49:39,809
I'd like to suggest a pottery
class for the internal training.

707
00:49:39,810 --> 00:49:40,889
What do you think?

708
00:49:41,342 --> 00:49:42,772
Our gallery

709
00:49:42,880 --> 00:49:44,880
is currently hosting
Yun Tae-jun's exhibition.

710
00:49:44,900 --> 00:49:48,256
Oh, the Chairman's favorite artist.

711
00:49:48,281 --> 00:49:50,248
He seems very famous.

712
00:49:50,273 --> 00:49:51,748
I went to see it over the weekend.

713
00:49:51,881 --> 00:49:53,647
Wow, it was packed.

714
00:49:53,880 --> 00:49:54,755
But

715
00:49:54,780 --> 00:49:56,395
can we really get

716
00:49:56,420 --> 00:49:57,645
such a famous artist?

717
00:49:57,670 --> 00:49:59,649
Even if we have a contract,

718
00:49:59,650 --> 00:50:01,166
getting him to teach an internal course

719
00:50:01,190 --> 00:50:02,285
won't be easy, right?

720
00:50:02,310 --> 00:50:04,553
I've already discussed it with the gallery.

721
00:50:04,943 --> 00:50:06,375
It'll help promote the artist too,

722
00:50:06,400 --> 00:50:07,860
so they're willing to cooperate.

723
00:50:10,545 --> 00:50:11,549
And the Chairman wants

724
00:50:11,550 --> 00:50:14,358
Mr. Yun to be more
involved with the company.

725
00:50:14,504 --> 00:50:15,855
We've confirmed that as well.

726
00:50:15,880 --> 00:50:16,915
Sounds good.

727
00:50:17,058 --> 00:50:18,785
Won-young, you take charge of this.

728
00:50:18,810 --> 00:50:20,027
Yes, Team Leader.

729
00:50:29,456 --> 00:50:30,456
Wow.

730
00:50:31,363 --> 00:50:32,871
This is totally my style.

731
00:50:34,250 --> 00:50:34,975
I'm taking it.

732
00:50:35,000 --> 00:50:36,000
Put it down.

733
00:50:43,694 --> 00:50:45,558
You donate them every year anyway.

734
00:50:45,583 --> 00:50:46,730
Can't I have just one?

735
00:50:47,254 --> 00:50:48,285
Just go home.

736
00:50:48,470 --> 00:50:49,941
I want to be alone.

737
00:50:52,681 --> 00:50:54,495
This one is great too.

738
00:50:54,986 --> 00:50:57,222
I didn't notice when you
were just a shop owner,

739
00:50:57,759 --> 00:50:59,479
but now that I know you're a famous artist,

740
00:50:59,535 --> 00:51:01,215
these dishes seem to sparkle.

741
00:51:02,250 --> 00:51:03,410
Are you going to put it down?

742
00:51:10,323 --> 00:51:12,417
Has Won-young contacted you lately?

743
00:51:19,171 --> 00:51:21,011
I told you, we're over.

744
00:51:21,081 --> 00:51:22,200
At this rate, Won-young

745
00:51:22,651 --> 00:51:24,347
is going to get tired and give up on you.

746
00:51:32,536 --> 00:51:34,393
Fine, I'm... I'm going.

747
00:51:34,807 --> 00:51:36,210
I'm going, I'm going.

748
00:51:36,235 --> 00:51:37,235
I'm out.

749
00:51:40,400 --> 00:51:41,400
Hey.

750
00:51:56,310 --> 00:51:58,534
If you're angry because you think

751
00:51:58,559 --> 00:52:00,339
I was faking my feelings for you,

752
00:52:03,465 --> 00:52:04,807
if that's why you can't forgive me,

753
00:52:04,831 --> 00:52:05,980
then that's just not fair.

754
00:52:30,530 --> 00:52:31,530
Hey.

755
00:52:31,847 --> 00:52:32,960
Hello?

756
00:52:33,159 --> 00:52:34,479
Hello, Mr. Yun.

757
00:52:34,504 --> 00:52:36,224
This is Manager Jeong from Taepyeong Group.

758
00:52:36,768 --> 00:52:38,260
Is this a good time to talk?

759
00:52:38,550 --> 00:52:39,503
Go ahead.

760
00:52:39,528 --> 00:52:41,705
Right, about the pottery class proposal

761
00:52:41,730 --> 00:52:44,268
I mentioned before. I
just emailed it to you.

762
00:52:44,612 --> 00:52:45,788
Please take a look

763
00:52:45,813 --> 00:52:47,117
and let us know what you think.

764
00:52:47,570 --> 00:52:48,170
Okay.

765
00:52:48,562 --> 00:52:49,874
Oh, and one more thing.

766
00:52:50,700 --> 00:52:53,300
You'll see it in the proposal,

767
00:52:54,851 --> 00:52:56,734
but the person in charge of this project

768
00:52:57,163 --> 00:52:58,290
is Ji Won-young.

769
00:52:58,887 --> 00:53:01,874
I thought I should let you know beforehand.

770
00:53:01,899 --> 00:53:03,663
Then I don't need to think about it.

771
00:53:04,620 --> 00:53:05,620
I refuse.

772
00:53:05,842 --> 00:53:06,842
What?

773
00:53:06,880 --> 00:53:07,880
Artist...

774
00:53:08,307 --> 00:53:09,307
Hello?

775
00:53:09,382 --> 00:53:10,382
Mr. Yun?

776
00:53:14,160 --> 00:53:15,440
See, I told you.

777
00:53:15,450 --> 00:53:16,898
I told you he wouldn't agree.

778
00:53:16,923 --> 00:53:19,507
That's why I said we shouldn't
put Won-young's name on it.

779
00:53:19,532 --> 00:53:21,453
Why were you so stubborn?

780
00:53:23,600 --> 00:53:25,234
I'll try to convince him one more time.

781
00:53:29,120 --> 00:53:30,120
I can do it.

782
00:53:41,732 --> 00:53:42,732
Ugh.

783
00:53:43,173 --> 00:53:44,420
Seriously.

784
00:53:44,445 --> 00:53:46,024
I really...

785
00:53:53,710 --> 00:53:55,548
I can't give up on you.

786
00:53:55,573 --> 00:53:57,142
I just can't.

787
00:53:58,499 --> 00:53:59,499
This is driving me crazy.

788
00:54:11,687 --> 00:54:12,800
Hello.

789
00:54:13,726 --> 00:54:15,093
Are you here to see Tae-jun?

790
00:54:15,296 --> 00:54:15,944
Yes.

791
00:54:16,040 --> 00:54:17,318
Do you have an appointment?

792
00:54:17,444 --> 00:54:18,340
He didn't mention anyone coming.

793
00:54:18,380 --> 00:54:20,429
He's not answering my calls,
so I just came by.

794
00:54:22,038 --> 00:54:23,585
I'm not sure if he'll see you.

795
00:54:24,022 --> 00:54:25,190
He is inside, though.

796
00:54:26,120 --> 00:54:27,120
Thank you.

797
00:54:28,956 --> 00:54:29,956
Excuse me.

798
00:54:33,636 --> 00:54:35,507
Did you do something bad to him?

799
00:54:36,478 --> 00:54:37,478
Yes.

800
00:54:38,178 --> 00:54:40,015
- Something very bad.
- Oh dear.

801
00:54:41,609 --> 00:54:43,210
Then you should probably give up.

802
00:54:43,828 --> 00:54:45,468
He's likely not going to change his mind.

803
00:54:45,539 --> 00:54:46,990
The wounds he's suffered...

804
00:54:47,015 --> 00:54:48,593
have only just begun to heal.

805
00:54:48,773 --> 00:54:49,960
What?

806
00:54:55,132 --> 00:54:56,132
Oh no.

807
00:55:09,440 --> 00:55:10,440
Sunbae!

808
00:55:12,340 --> 00:55:13,340
Ji Won-young.

809
00:55:14,304 --> 00:55:15,304
Are you hurt?

810
00:55:15,929 --> 00:55:16,929
Don't worry.

811
00:55:17,680 --> 00:55:19,382
He didn't get hit.

812
00:55:19,762 --> 00:55:21,572
He just got dizzy and lost his balance.

813
00:55:21,597 --> 00:55:23,234
I managed to catch him, but...

814
00:55:23,396 --> 00:55:24,835
I'm asking if YOU are hurt.

815
00:55:27,476 --> 00:55:28,593
I'm fine.

816
00:55:28,771 --> 00:55:30,091
Get him to the hospital, quickly.

817
00:55:32,194 --> 00:55:33,194
Sunbae.

818
00:55:33,503 --> 00:55:34,503
Sunbae.

819
00:55:46,838 --> 00:55:49,057
Let us know if you feel any discomfort.

820
00:55:58,800 --> 00:56:00,892
Orthostatic hypotension? How embarrassing.

821
00:56:01,593 --> 00:56:03,658
That's why I told you to stop drinking.

822
00:56:03,683 --> 00:56:04,683
That's enough.

823
00:56:04,916 --> 00:56:07,557
The doctor already lectured me plenty.

824
00:56:10,860 --> 00:56:11,744
Thank you.

825
00:56:11,769 --> 00:56:14,209
If it weren't for you, Won-young,
it could have been serious.

826
00:56:14,455 --> 00:56:15,947
I'm just glad you're okay.

827
00:56:16,920 --> 00:56:19,361
Hmm... but what do we do now?

828
00:56:20,294 --> 00:56:22,454
The deadline for the pieces
is the day after tomorrow.

829
00:56:23,377 --> 00:56:24,889
We need to start the firing

830
00:56:24,890 --> 00:56:26,549
by tonight to make it on time.

831
00:56:26,550 --> 00:56:27,569
Don't worry about it.

832
00:56:27,913 --> 00:56:29,467
Sunbae, just focus on getting better.

833
00:56:30,200 --> 00:56:31,514
- I'll handle it.
- Hey.

834
00:56:31,577 --> 00:56:33,217
You can't do all that by yourself.

835
00:56:33,320 --> 00:56:34,320
Well...

836
00:56:34,794 --> 00:56:37,022
Can I help?

837
00:56:37,918 --> 00:56:39,280
Tomorrow is Sunday,

838
00:56:39,305 --> 00:56:40,367
and I don't have anything special planned.

839
00:56:40,391 --> 00:56:41,391
You, Won-young?

840
00:56:41,710 --> 00:56:43,011
Are you sure?

841
00:56:43,036 --> 00:56:44,288
If I can be of any help.

842
00:56:48,131 --> 00:56:49,702
You should go get treated first.

843
00:56:50,780 --> 00:56:51,950
I'm fine.

844
00:56:52,878 --> 00:56:53,878
Follow me.

845
00:57:05,724 --> 00:57:07,686
I didn't really need a bandage.

846
00:57:08,960 --> 00:57:09,960
Thank you.

847
00:57:10,624 --> 00:57:11,499
Sunbae Geon-hui...

848
00:57:11,524 --> 00:57:13,110
- Thank you for protecting him.
- Don't mention it.

849
00:57:13,134 --> 00:57:14,827
Anyone would have done the same.

850
00:57:17,105 --> 00:57:18,105
Did you come today

851
00:57:19,483 --> 00:57:20,944
because of that proposal?

852
00:57:21,967 --> 00:57:23,210
Well, yes.

853
00:57:24,332 --> 00:57:25,332
But isn't the work

854
00:57:25,588 --> 00:57:27,444
at the studio more urgent?

855
00:57:27,469 --> 00:57:28,469
No, thanks.

856
00:57:28,830 --> 00:57:29,830
If I really can't do it,

857
00:57:29,999 --> 00:57:31,370
I'll find someone else to help.

858
00:57:31,433 --> 00:57:32,433
Listen...

859
00:57:33,064 --> 00:57:35,350
I'm not offering to help
because of the proposal.

860
00:57:47,390 --> 00:57:48,522
Hey, Professor.

861
00:57:54,870 --> 00:57:55,870
No.

862
00:57:55,895 --> 00:57:57,233
I'll have it in on time.

863
00:57:57,921 --> 00:57:59,186
By tomorrow night.

864
00:58:10,709 --> 00:58:11,709
I really

865
00:58:12,548 --> 00:58:14,397
didn't want to ask this,

866
00:58:16,132 --> 00:58:18,296
but I'm in a bit of a bind.

867
00:58:21,960 --> 00:58:23,135
Can you help me?

868
00:58:23,160 --> 00:58:23,895
Of course.

869
00:58:23,920 --> 00:58:24,920
No problem.

870
00:58:26,001 --> 00:58:27,001
Let's go.

871
00:58:32,007 --> 00:58:33,807
Were you planning to
do all this by yourself?

872
00:58:34,742 --> 00:58:36,262
You're going to run yourself ragged...

873
00:58:38,409 --> 00:58:39,409
I'm sorry.

874
00:58:40,842 --> 00:58:42,562
I don't have the right to worry about that.

875
00:58:51,234 --> 00:58:52,234
Go change first.

876
00:59:05,850 --> 00:59:07,110
Well...

877
00:59:11,830 --> 00:59:13,510
I'll be over by the kiln.

878
00:59:13,663 --> 00:59:15,360
Call me if you need anything.

879
00:59:15,385 --> 00:59:16,741
Don't worry about this part.

880
00:59:32,413 --> 00:59:33,467
I'm all done.

881
00:59:35,590 --> 00:59:36,671
Good work.

882
00:59:37,300 --> 00:59:38,528
You can go take a break now.

883
00:59:38,553 --> 00:59:39,734
If there's anything else, leave it to me!

884
00:59:39,758 --> 00:59:40,764
No, thanks.

885
00:59:41,194 --> 00:59:42,960
Go rest over there.

886
00:59:44,265 --> 00:59:45,265
I'm fine.

887
01:00:08,148 --> 01:00:09,835
In case another spark flies out,

888
01:00:11,551 --> 01:00:13,139
I can block it for you.

889
01:00:14,500 --> 01:00:15,678
That must have hurt.

890
01:00:17,989 --> 01:00:19,710
No matter how you got hurt,

891
01:00:22,999 --> 01:00:24,499
a wound is still a wound.

892
01:00:42,460 --> 01:00:43,936
Since we have some time,

893
01:00:44,640 --> 01:00:46,483
let's take a look at that proposal.

894
01:00:48,033 --> 01:00:49,506
What proposal?

895
01:00:49,621 --> 01:00:51,647
The pottery class the
company wants to start.

896
01:00:53,147 --> 01:00:54,540
Isn't that why

897
01:00:55,490 --> 01:00:56,717
you came here?

898
01:01:03,690 --> 01:01:04,540
Why are you being like this?

899
01:01:04,565 --> 01:01:05,135
Like what?

900
01:01:05,160 --> 01:01:06,160
You're angry right now.

901
01:01:06,161 --> 01:01:07,600
What right do I have to be angry?

902
01:01:08,835 --> 01:01:10,913
But honestly, it feels unfair.

903
01:01:11,636 --> 01:01:13,546
I told you I didn't help you for that.

904
01:01:13,571 --> 01:01:15,147
No matter how many times I
say it, you won't believe me.

905
01:01:15,171 --> 01:01:16,624
You just don't trust anything I say.

906
01:01:19,963 --> 01:01:21,350
I'm doing this out of gratitude.

907
01:01:23,085 --> 01:01:24,492
Because I knew if I offered to pay you,

908
01:01:24,516 --> 01:01:25,710
you'd just get angry.

909
01:01:27,668 --> 01:01:29,186
What you need most right now

910
01:01:31,455 --> 01:01:32,749
is that opportunity, isn't it?

911
01:01:33,170 --> 01:01:35,585
No, that's not what I need most.

912
01:01:37,830 --> 01:01:39,921
You don't even know
why I started that project.

913
01:01:41,951 --> 01:01:43,296
Just forget it.

914
01:01:44,006 --> 01:01:46,006
I didn't do it to get
anything in return anyway.

915
01:01:48,514 --> 01:01:49,858
I'm going to sleep.

916
01:01:50,701 --> 01:01:52,499
Call me if you need anything.

917
01:02:08,960 --> 01:02:10,538
Unrequited love really sucks.

918
01:02:11,632 --> 01:02:13,436
It makes you so pathetic.

919
01:03:21,171 --> 01:03:22,350
As for me...

920
01:03:23,632 --> 01:03:25,819
even though I hate you so much,

921
01:03:28,358 --> 01:03:29,631
I still love you.

922
01:03:31,827 --> 01:03:33,288
It's driving me crazy.

923
01:05:10,811 --> 01:05:12,068
Is it around here?

924
01:05:37,760 --> 01:05:38,967
Ah, no.

925
01:05:50,457 --> 01:05:52,350
I'm getting so childish.

926
01:05:54,826 --> 01:05:56,381
Well, I like childish things too.

927
01:06:17,070 --> 01:06:18,070
Hey.

928
01:06:18,193 --> 01:06:18,904
Won-young.

929
01:06:19,050 --> 01:06:20,015
This is Park Geon-hui.

930
01:06:20,040 --> 01:06:21,279
Tae-jun's sunbae.

931
01:06:21,631 --> 01:06:22,436
Hello.

932
01:06:22,461 --> 01:06:23,225
<i>I got your number</i>

933
01:06:23,250 --> 01:06:24,299
from Dong-hee.

934
01:06:24,300 --> 01:06:25,700
I hope I'm not being too intrusive.

935
01:06:26,250 --> 01:06:27,272
Not at all.

936
01:06:27,666 --> 01:06:28,936
Are you feeling better?

937
01:06:28,961 --> 01:06:30,733
Oh, thanks to you.

938
01:06:30,816 --> 01:06:32,506
I'm actually calling about that.

939
01:06:32,608 --> 01:06:35,110
The day after tomorrow is Christmas Eve.

940
01:06:35,135 --> 01:06:35,945
Do you have plans?

941
01:06:35,970 --> 01:06:37,131
What's happening on Christmas Eve?

942
01:06:37,155 --> 01:06:39,009
<i>Well, my wife</i>

943
01:06:39,010 --> 01:06:40,562
<i>wants to treat you to dinner to say thanks.</i>

944
01:06:40,586 --> 01:06:42,123
We're having a small party.

945
01:06:42,389 --> 01:06:43,499
Dong-hee and Ho-tae said they'd come too.

946
01:06:43,500 --> 01:06:44,500
Will...

947
01:06:44,892 --> 01:06:46,154
the Boss be there too?

948
01:06:46,730 --> 01:06:47,873
<i>Tae-jun?</i>

949
01:06:48,940 --> 01:06:51,842
Well, he has an important date that day.

950
01:06:53,171 --> 01:06:55,178
He said he'd come
over as soon as it's over.

951
01:06:55,600 --> 01:06:56,889
<i>But he probably won't
make it until after midnight.</i>

952
01:06:56,890 --> 01:06:57,890
Then I'll be there.

953
01:06:57,959 --> 01:06:58,490
Okay.

954
01:06:58,711 --> 01:07:00,511
I'll text you the location
once it's decided.

955
01:07:00,550 --> 01:07:01,162
Okay.

956
01:07:01,311 --> 01:07:02,410
Thank you.

957
01:07:17,943 --> 01:07:19,686
Is it really okay if I don't go tomorrow?

958
01:07:20,532 --> 01:07:21,717
Don't worry.

959
01:07:21,834 --> 01:07:22,931
Everything you needed to do,

960
01:07:22,955 --> 01:07:24,193
Won-young already did for you.

961
01:07:24,310 --> 01:07:25,310
Really?

962
01:07:25,423 --> 01:07:27,279
Wow, I'm so grateful.

963
01:07:29,773 --> 01:07:30,773
By the way,

964
01:07:31,130 --> 01:07:33,404
how are things going with Won-young?

965
01:07:34,711 --> 01:07:35,998
What do you mean?

966
01:07:36,390 --> 01:07:37,310
I told you, we broke up.

967
01:07:37,335 --> 01:07:38,335
You guy.

968
01:07:38,470 --> 01:07:39,650
You think I was completely unconscious

969
01:07:39,660 --> 01:07:41,000
when I fainted, don't you?

970
01:07:41,632 --> 01:07:42,632
These ears

971
01:07:42,657 --> 01:07:44,178
were wide open the whole time.

972
01:07:44,940 --> 01:07:47,299
Your long-time sunbae fainted,

973
01:07:47,300 --> 01:07:48,660
and yet you only had eyes for him.

974
01:07:49,129 --> 01:07:50,936
I heard he did something really bad to you.

975
01:07:51,600 --> 01:07:53,400
Is it so bad that you'll
never see him again?

976
01:07:53,807 --> 01:07:54,807
He...

977
01:07:56,162 --> 01:07:57,310
lied to me.

978
01:07:58,182 --> 01:08:00,084
He had an ulterior motive.

979
01:08:01,696 --> 01:08:04,053
He approached me on purpose from the start.

980
01:08:06,022 --> 01:08:07,356
And then he faked his feelings for me.

981
01:08:07,380 --> 01:08:08,381
Won-young?

982
01:08:08,928 --> 01:08:10,428
He faked his feelings?

983
01:08:11,817 --> 01:08:13,045
Of course he says he didn't.

984
01:08:14,590 --> 01:08:16,404
But who would admit to something like that?

985
01:08:17,861 --> 01:08:19,319
My wife always says this.

986
01:08:19,428 --> 01:08:20,637
Whenever I mess up,

987
01:08:20,662 --> 01:08:22,905
she first thinks, "I wish someone
would just take this guy away."

988
01:08:22,929 --> 01:08:23,929
But then she thinks,

989
01:08:24,108 --> 01:08:25,561
"Could I live without him?"

990
01:08:26,221 --> 01:08:27,301
As soon as she thinks that,

991
01:08:27,397 --> 01:08:28,900
she immediately calms down.

992
01:08:29,220 --> 01:08:30,220
And then she forgives me.

993
01:08:31,662 --> 01:08:32,771
Why are you telling
me this all of a sudden?

994
01:08:32,795 --> 01:08:34,609
Can you really go the rest of your life
without seeing him?

995
01:08:34,633 --> 01:08:35,633
From where I'm sitting,

996
01:08:35,928 --> 01:08:37,295
you don't look okay at all.

997
01:08:39,678 --> 01:08:40,529
Stop it.

998
01:08:40,554 --> 01:08:42,154
You know I'm always on your side, right?

999
01:08:43,126 --> 01:08:45,536
I haven't said anything
like this for two years.

1000
01:08:46,084 --> 01:08:47,427
So I'll just say one thing.

1001
01:08:48,940 --> 01:08:49,940
Tae-jun.

1002
01:08:50,522 --> 01:08:51,730
The past...

1003
01:08:51,923 --> 01:08:52,923
just let it go.

1004
01:08:54,319 --> 01:08:56,239
If you miss out on
something else because of it,

1005
01:08:57,876 --> 01:08:59,357
won't that be too painful?

1006
01:09:03,498 --> 01:09:04,498
But anyway...

1007
01:09:04,857 --> 01:09:05,857
you'll figure it out.

1008
01:09:05,882 --> 01:09:06,882
Right?

1009
01:09:15,160 --> 01:09:16,610
I'm sorry, Boss.

1010
01:09:17,630 --> 01:09:19,576
How was I supposed
to know I'd fall for you?

1011
01:09:22,320 --> 01:09:23,951
I only did it because I didn't know.

1012
01:09:26,963 --> 01:09:27,963
As for me...

1013
01:09:30,351 --> 01:09:32,161
even though I hate you so much,

1014
01:09:35,209 --> 01:09:36,209
I still love you.

1015
01:09:38,608 --> 01:09:39,900
It's driving me crazy.

1016
01:10:01,709 --> 01:10:03,514
Shouldn't you go home for a visit?

1017
01:10:03,539 --> 01:10:05,318
They wouldn't want me there anyway.

1018
01:10:06,424 --> 01:10:07,695
I called them.

1019
01:10:07,720 --> 01:10:08,720
Good job.

1020
01:10:09,818 --> 01:10:11,443
Oh, geez.

1021
01:10:11,468 --> 01:10:12,468
Drink some water.

1022
01:10:49,867 --> 01:10:52,187
What kind of father would
treat his own child like that...

1023
01:11:01,290 --> 01:11:02,330
Let me tell you something.

1024
01:11:02,498 --> 01:11:03,620
Our Dong-hee,

1025
01:11:03,850 --> 01:11:05,749
whether he likes women or men,

1026
01:11:05,750 --> 01:11:06,998
I don't care.

1027
01:11:07,076 --> 01:11:08,220
I'll always

1028
01:11:08,245 --> 01:11:11,459
support you in finding your happiness.

1029
01:11:11,574 --> 01:11:13,795
If you get kicked out,
just come straight here.

1030
01:11:15,759 --> 01:11:16,759
Ma'am.

1031
01:11:29,875 --> 01:11:30,875
Dong-hee.

1032
01:11:32,437 --> 01:11:33,437
Go ahead and eat.

1033
01:11:34,752 --> 01:11:35,752
I'm leaving.

1034
01:11:39,770 --> 01:11:40,770
Go on in.

1035
01:11:56,593 --> 01:11:57,593
Ma'am,

1036
01:12:01,080 --> 01:12:02,080
I'm sorry.

1037
01:12:08,420 --> 01:12:09,897
Hey, wait for me.

1038
01:12:18,222 --> 01:12:19,532
Remember we agreed

1039
01:12:19,790 --> 01:12:22,110
to close the cafe early today
and go look at coffee beans?

1040
01:12:37,870 --> 01:12:38,870
What are you doing?

1041
01:12:42,026 --> 01:12:43,026
Hey.

1042
01:12:43,578 --> 01:12:44,578
What do you

1043
01:12:46,028 --> 01:12:46,558
think?

1044
01:12:46,583 --> 01:12:47,123
What?

1045
01:12:47,148 --> 01:12:48,264
Do you... want to date?

1046
01:12:51,590 --> 01:12:53,599
Man, that really hit me where it hurts...

1047
01:12:53,600 --> 01:12:55,350
You're just so annoying.

1048
01:12:56,693 --> 01:12:57,319
But

1049
01:12:57,344 --> 01:12:58,864
is your injury from the accident okay?

1050
01:13:00,010 --> 01:13:01,170
It hurts.

1051
01:13:02,756 --> 01:13:03,713
About once

1052
01:13:03,738 --> 01:13:04,738
a year.

1053
01:13:15,959 --> 01:13:18,608
I didn't think I should
ask, so I never did.

1054
01:13:20,363 --> 01:13:22,083
Why were you riding a motorcycle back then?

1055
01:13:23,045 --> 01:13:25,019
Even if you fought to keep swimming,

1056
01:13:25,020 --> 01:13:26,629
you wouldn't have gone that far, would you?

1057
01:13:26,653 --> 01:13:29,022
It was to make myself
look more like a thug.

1058
01:13:37,733 --> 01:13:39,253
After you went to university in Seoul,

1059
01:13:39,678 --> 01:13:40,904
I had a hard time.

1060
01:13:41,117 --> 01:13:42,826
I thought I'd be fine if I didn't see you.

1061
01:13:44,860 --> 01:13:46,100
But I wasn't fine at all.

1062
01:13:48,123 --> 01:13:49,608
I thought I was going crazy.

1063
01:13:50,530 --> 01:13:51,690
How could I feel that way

1064
01:13:51,876 --> 01:13:53,556
about a close hyung from the neighborhood?

1065
01:13:55,630 --> 01:13:57,990
I thought if I lived like trash
and made a mess of my life,

1066
01:13:58,400 --> 01:13:59,400
then later,

1067
01:13:59,531 --> 01:14:02,295
even if I wanted to confess so badly,

1068
01:14:02,462 --> 01:14:04,240
I'd be too ashamed to say it.

1069
01:14:04,460 --> 01:14:05,255
But that was all nonsense.

1070
01:14:05,280 --> 01:14:06,404
Things you can't hold back,

1071
01:14:07,610 --> 01:14:09,397
you just can't hold back.

1072
01:14:16,850 --> 01:14:17,850
Why...

1073
01:14:18,510 --> 01:14:19,616
didn't you tell me to get lost?

1074
01:14:19,640 --> 01:14:20,640
It's a bit scary.

1075
01:14:24,217 --> 01:14:25,340
If you find it annoying,

1076
01:14:25,467 --> 01:14:26,717
you can keep rejecting me.

1077
01:14:27,940 --> 01:14:30,545
I'm going to keep pestering you anyway.

1078
01:14:32,440 --> 01:14:34,850
I need to wash this.

1079
01:14:57,010 --> 01:14:58,412
I'm from General Affairs.

1080
01:14:58,437 --> 01:14:59,845
I'm here to get the warehouse key.

1081
01:14:59,870 --> 01:15:01,147
Okay, please wait a moment.

1082
01:15:03,433 --> 01:15:04,772
Excuse me, the warehouse key...

1083
01:15:04,797 --> 01:15:06,373
Okay, I understand.

1084
01:15:08,120 --> 01:15:11,045
The person with the key just stepped out.

1085
01:15:11,070 --> 01:15:12,710
They asked if you could wait ten minutes.

1086
01:15:12,928 --> 01:15:14,420
I'll wait here then.

1087
01:15:14,610 --> 01:15:15,610
Okay.

1088
01:15:25,290 --> 01:15:26,290
Tae-jun.

1089
01:15:33,279 --> 01:15:34,279
Huh?

1090
01:15:35,140 --> 01:15:36,045
Let's go.

1091
01:15:36,154 --> 01:15:37,154
We're going to be late.

1092
01:16:13,400 --> 01:16:14,373
[Insurance Processing Completed]

1093
01:16:21,248 --> 01:16:22,420
Wow...

1094
01:16:22,445 --> 01:16:24,498
The report is full of curses!

1095
01:16:25,930 --> 01:16:26,930
What?

1096
01:16:29,252 --> 01:16:30,252
Are you okay?

1097
01:16:30,834 --> 01:16:32,209
Yeah, I'm fine.

1098
01:16:32,466 --> 01:16:34,131
It's Christmas Eve, don't you have plans?

1099
01:16:34,379 --> 01:16:35,379
Ah, right.

1100
01:16:35,654 --> 01:16:36,974
Didn't you take half the day off?

1101
01:16:38,936 --> 01:16:41,170
I feel bad

1102
01:16:41,428 --> 01:16:42,948
leaving you to do the inventory alone.

1103
01:16:44,248 --> 01:16:45,320
I'll help you.

1104
01:16:47,010 --> 01:16:48,010
What?

1105
01:16:48,088 --> 01:16:49,264
Don't you have a date?

1106
01:16:52,206 --> 01:16:53,240
It's cancelled.

1107
01:17:04,287 --> 01:17:05,350
Yun Tae-jun.

1108
01:17:05,959 --> 01:17:07,303
Wait for me.

1109
01:17:12,000 --> 01:17:14,397
- Hey.
<i>- Did something happen between you and Won-young?</i>

1110
01:17:15,350 --> 01:17:16,154
What do you mean?

1111
01:17:16,350 --> 01:17:18,412
<i>Won-young called and
said he can't make it today.</i>

1112
01:17:19,120 --> 01:17:20,120
Why so suddenly?

1113
01:17:20,541 --> 01:17:22,811
<i>He said he has a lot
of work at the company.</i>

1114
01:17:23,560 --> 01:17:25,967
<i>But he sounded terrible,
so I thought I'd ask.</i>

1115
01:17:27,192 --> 01:17:29,601
<i>I wondered if he was just using
work as an excuse because of you.</i>

1116
01:17:29,625 --> 01:17:30,625
Let's talk later.

1117
01:17:45,310 --> 01:17:47,064
The quantities have
all been checked, right?

1118
01:17:47,088 --> 01:17:47,852
Yes.

1119
01:17:47,877 --> 01:17:49,997
I just need to subtract
the spare quantities.

1120
01:17:53,690 --> 01:17:55,100
(Boss)

1121
01:18:05,198 --> 01:18:06,198
Answer it.

1122
01:18:07,600 --> 01:18:08,600
It's okay.

1123
01:18:08,932 --> 01:18:10,526
I don't have to take it.

1124
01:18:24,304 --> 01:18:25,915
(I heard you can't make it today?)

1125
01:18:27,026 --> 01:18:28,680
(If it's because you're working late, )

1126
01:18:29,675 --> 01:18:31,205
(I'll come pick you up. Let me know.)

1127
01:18:32,390 --> 01:18:33,620
(I'm in Seoul right now.)

1128
01:19:13,346 --> 01:19:14,430
I'm curious.

1129
01:19:19,112 --> 01:19:20,306
That look on your face right now...

1130
01:19:20,330 --> 01:19:21,459
In the five years we dated,

1131
01:19:21,460 --> 01:19:24,213
why did I never see it once?

1132
01:19:24,504 --> 01:19:26,479
Who is it that makes you look like that?

1133
01:19:29,734 --> 01:19:30,734
Go on in.

1134
01:19:30,909 --> 01:19:32,271
- I need to make a call.
- Yun Tae-jun.

1135
01:19:32,295 --> 01:19:33,295
Stop it...

1136
01:19:35,406 --> 01:19:37,276
I don't have any feelings for you anymore.

1137
01:19:39,667 --> 01:19:40,955
Just stay quiet.

1138
01:19:54,290 --> 01:19:56,041
<i>The person you are
calling is not available.</i>

1139
01:19:56,065 --> 01:19:57,666
<i>Please leave a message...</i>

1140
01:19:58,940 --> 01:20:00,274
(I heard you can't make it today?
If it's because you're working

1141
01:20:00,298 --> 01:20:01,632
late, I'll come pick you up. Let
me know. I'm in Seoul right now.)

1142
01:20:02,770 --> 01:20:03,770
Mr. Yun.

1143
01:20:03,846 --> 01:20:04,970
Everything is ready.

1144
01:20:05,049 --> 01:20:06,292
We're about to start the briefing.

1145
01:20:06,316 --> 01:20:07,316
Okay.

1146
01:20:26,270 --> 01:20:28,770
(Boss)

1147
01:20:36,490 --> 01:20:39,259
Starting a pottery class
that's close to nature.

1148
01:20:39,260 --> 01:20:41,540
- It will not only improve the corporate image...
- Hello?

1149
01:20:43,039 --> 01:20:44,039
<i>Hello?</i>

1150
01:20:45,823 --> 01:20:46,823
Ji Won-young.

1151
01:20:51,541 --> 01:20:52,948
Don't hang up. Wait for me.

1152
01:20:54,462 --> 01:20:55,462
Excuse me.

1153
01:20:55,487 --> 01:20:56,807
I have an emergency.

1154
01:21:07,183 --> 01:21:08,183
So annoying.

1155
01:21:10,217 --> 01:21:11,897
Why haven't you been answering your phone?

1156
01:21:12,048 --> 01:21:13,048
<i>I was busy.</i>

1157
01:21:13,455 --> 01:21:14,570
Why are you calling?

1158
01:21:14,595 --> 01:21:16,355
<i>Shouldn't you have at
least sent me a message?</i>

1159
01:21:16,379 --> 01:21:17,549
Didn't you get my message?

1160
01:21:17,601 --> 01:21:19,561
<i>You haven't been answering
my calls either, Boss.</i>

1161
01:21:19,670 --> 01:21:21,729
And have you ever sent me a single message?

1162
01:21:22,157 --> 01:21:23,157
I understand.

1163
01:21:24,520 --> 01:21:25,550
About the party tonight,

1164
01:21:25,651 --> 01:21:26,750
I heard you can't make it.

1165
01:21:27,205 --> 01:21:27,901
Is that right?

1166
01:21:28,140 --> 01:21:29,776
I already called them and let them know.

1167
01:21:29,801 --> 01:21:31,088
They said they understood.

1168
01:21:31,113 --> 01:21:32,823
I can pick you up around ten tonight.

1169
01:21:33,280 --> 01:21:34,360
I'm in Seoul right now.

1170
01:21:34,971 --> 01:21:35,925
No, thanks.

1171
01:21:35,950 --> 01:21:37,534
Will you not be finished by then?

1172
01:21:37,830 --> 01:21:39,346
- Then I'll wait...
- No.

1173
01:21:44,403 --> 01:21:45,403
It's just...

1174
01:21:48,671 --> 01:21:50,198
I don't want to see you, Boss.

1175
01:21:50,440 --> 01:21:51,660
What did you

1176
01:21:54,300 --> 01:21:55,310
just say?

1177
01:21:55,605 --> 01:21:56,615
I'm hanging up.

1178
01:22:27,880 --> 01:22:29,400
Are you the owner of Moon Jar Pottery?

1179
01:22:29,750 --> 01:22:31,315
My name is Ji Won-young.

1180
01:22:31,534 --> 01:22:33,294
I'm twenty-seven, and
I'm looking for a job.

1181
01:22:33,871 --> 01:22:34,871
I'm choosing this one.

1182
01:22:35,099 --> 01:22:36,099
To me,

1183
01:22:36,362 --> 01:22:38,924
it looks like someone who
bravely overcame everything.

1184
01:22:41,170 --> 01:22:42,170
I can't...

1185
01:22:43,440 --> 01:22:44,893
I like you, Boss.

1186
01:22:47,157 --> 01:22:49,037
I was just being presumptuous

1187
01:22:50,224 --> 01:22:51,224
when I confessed to you.

1188
01:22:51,249 --> 01:22:52,249
I'm sorry.

1189
01:23:01,565 --> 01:23:03,165
I finally feel like I can breathe again.

1190
01:23:03,901 --> 01:23:06,221
Can you really go the rest of your life
without seeing him?

1191
01:23:06,639 --> 01:23:07,639
From where I'm sitting,

1192
01:23:08,002 --> 01:23:09,401
you don't look okay at all.

1193
01:24:07,616 --> 01:24:08,616
Why?

1194
01:24:10,767 --> 01:24:12,045
Why don't you want to see me?

1195
01:24:12,070 --> 01:24:13,790
Isn't it better if we don't see each other?

1196
01:24:13,934 --> 01:24:15,374
Didn't you say you were tired of me?

1197
01:24:15,570 --> 01:24:17,475
I have feelings too. I get hurt.

1198
01:24:17,500 --> 01:24:19,060
So why are you suddenly hurt...

1199
01:24:19,085 --> 01:24:20,573
Why is it okay for that person?

1200
01:24:20,598 --> 01:24:22,678
Why did you go all the way
to Seoul on Christmas Eve

1201
01:24:22,963 --> 01:24:24,557
just to meet him alone?

1202
01:24:24,734 --> 01:24:25,308
Who?

1203
01:24:25,427 --> 01:24:26,721
I saw him get into the taxi.

1204
01:24:27,418 --> 01:24:29,865
Even though he hurt you so much,

1205
01:24:29,890 --> 01:24:31,130
you can forgive him completely.

1206
01:24:31,360 --> 01:24:32,360
But me,

1207
01:24:32,941 --> 01:24:35,580
I'm just someone you hate so much
you'll never forgive me, right?

1208
01:24:36,627 --> 01:24:38,541
I don't like people who hate me either.

1209
01:24:39,666 --> 01:24:41,127
I'm really giving up now.

1210
01:24:54,089 --> 01:24:55,268
What is this?

1211
01:24:55,293 --> 01:24:56,293
Look.

1212
01:25:00,254 --> 01:25:01,338
It's a special exhibition

1213
01:25:01,534 --> 01:25:03,423
organized by my mentor for his students.

1214
01:25:03,448 --> 01:25:04,578
I couldn't miss it.

1215
01:25:04,924 --> 01:25:06,786
Today was the only time that worked,

1216
01:25:06,811 --> 01:25:08,501
so that's why the meeting was today.

1217
01:25:08,868 --> 01:25:11,068
I was going to go to the
meeting at headquarters alone,

1218
01:25:12,077 --> 01:25:13,977
but he just showed up
without saying anything.

1219
01:25:14,002 --> 01:25:15,002
And

1220
01:25:16,135 --> 01:25:17,776
sharing the taxi

1221
01:25:19,113 --> 01:25:20,633
was to make it to the meeting on time.

1222
01:25:20,815 --> 01:25:21,960
It was unavoidable.

1223
01:25:25,328 --> 01:25:26,148
Should I keep going?

1224
01:25:26,173 --> 01:25:27,173
Then

1225
01:25:28,737 --> 01:25:30,417
while you're preparing for the exhibition,

1226
01:25:31,280 --> 01:25:33,320
- you'll keep running into him...
- I'm sure I will.

1227
01:25:34,174 --> 01:25:35,174
But

1228
01:25:36,234 --> 01:25:38,635
he means absolutely nothing to me anymore.

1229
01:25:44,635 --> 01:25:46,010
You said before...

1230
01:25:47,205 --> 01:25:48,784
that you needed something else most.

1231
01:25:49,291 --> 01:25:50,470
Can I ask

1232
01:25:52,479 --> 01:25:53,885
what that is?

1233
01:25:53,910 --> 01:25:54,910
That is...

1234
01:25:56,690 --> 01:25:58,112
to be forgiven

1235
01:25:58,830 --> 01:25:59,950
for lying to you.

1236
01:25:59,990 --> 01:26:01,877
If I forgive you,

1237
01:26:03,803 --> 01:26:05,103
what happens then?

1238
01:26:05,658 --> 01:26:07,038
If you forgive me,

1239
01:26:08,323 --> 01:26:09,338
I'll do

1240
01:26:10,069 --> 01:26:12,049
everything I can to make it up to you.

1241
01:26:12,192 --> 01:26:13,799
If you want me to quit,

1242
01:26:14,213 --> 01:26:15,380
I will.

1243
01:26:16,324 --> 01:26:17,838
If you want financial compensation,

1244
01:26:17,877 --> 01:26:18,877
no matter what,

1245
01:26:19,725 --> 01:26:21,393
I'll work my whole life to pay you back.

1246
01:26:24,166 --> 01:26:25,416
Is that all?

1247
01:26:28,372 --> 01:26:31,252
If you want me to never
show my face again...

1248
01:26:33,755 --> 01:26:34,755
then I'll...

1249
01:26:35,445 --> 01:26:36,682
try to do that too.

1250
01:26:39,401 --> 01:26:40,470
Then let's do this...

1251
01:26:42,815 --> 01:26:44,455
I accept your apology.

1252
01:26:46,660 --> 01:26:47,660
So now,

1253
01:26:49,980 --> 01:26:51,315
it's my turn to say

1254
01:26:52,461 --> 01:26:53,674
what I want, right?

1255
01:26:54,840 --> 01:26:55,840
No.

1256
01:26:55,865 --> 01:26:56,865
I'm sorry.

1257
01:26:57,957 --> 01:26:59,064
I lied again.

1258
01:26:59,231 --> 01:27:00,580
Everything else was true,

1259
01:27:00,605 --> 01:27:02,729
but never showing my face to you again...

1260
01:27:03,670 --> 01:27:04,670
I can't do that.

1261
01:27:05,500 --> 01:27:06,860
Please let me see you

1262
01:27:07,360 --> 01:27:09,166
every now and then, like this.

1263
01:27:09,721 --> 01:27:11,143
I'll be like air.

1264
01:27:11,561 --> 01:27:12,987
You won't even notice I'm there...

1265
01:27:22,110 --> 01:27:23,110
I'm sorry

1266
01:27:25,201 --> 01:27:26,561
for making things so hard for you.

1267
01:27:27,770 --> 01:27:28,770
Boss.

1268
01:27:29,918 --> 01:27:31,528
When you said you didn't want to see me,

1269
01:27:31,553 --> 01:27:32,659
I realized...

1270
01:27:35,300 --> 01:27:37,198
it's not your feelings
that are the problem,

1271
01:27:38,276 --> 01:27:39,380
it's mine.

1272
01:27:41,215 --> 01:27:42,955
What I want from you

1273
01:27:45,037 --> 01:27:46,401
isn't an apology.

1274
01:27:48,190 --> 01:27:49,455
It's a relationship.

1275
01:28:25,519 --> 01:28:26,519
Won-young.

1276
01:28:30,030 --> 01:28:31,030
Should we...

1277
01:28:34,955 --> 01:28:36,190
start over?

1278
01:29:26,420 --> 01:29:27,971
(Hey, where are you?)

1279
01:29:28,141 --> 01:29:29,141
(Have you left yet?)

1280
01:29:29,299 --> 01:29:29,942
(What about Won-young?)

1281
01:29:29,967 --> 01:29:31,221
(You guys are coming together, right?)

1282
01:29:31,245 --> 01:29:32,925
(Hey, are you not checking your messages?)

1283
01:29:33,092 --> 01:29:34,314
(Did something happen to Won-young?)

1284
01:29:34,338 --> 01:29:35,534
(I'm asking where you are!)

1285
01:29:35,749 --> 01:29:37,276
(Hey!)

1286
01:30:22,742 --> 01:30:24,734
Right before our eyes.

1287
01:30:25,449 --> 01:30:28,190
♪ Time has stopped ♪

1288
01:30:29,060 --> 01:30:31,120
♪ Just us ♪

1289
01:30:32,022 --> 01:30:34,273
♪ Just the two of us ♪

1290
01:30:34,648 --> 01:30:38,151
- ♪ For our memories ♪
- Merry Christmas.

1291
01:30:48,452 --> 01:30:49,452
Hey.

1292
01:30:51,050 --> 01:30:52,050
Are you crazy?

1293
01:30:52,437 --> 01:30:53,760
Drink your own, seriously.

1294
01:31:07,812 --> 01:31:08,812
Hey.

1295
01:31:09,540 --> 01:31:10,885
Stop taking mine.

1296
01:31:10,910 --> 01:31:12,570
I told you to eat your own!

1297
01:31:13,310 --> 01:31:14,890
Just let me do this one thing.

1298
01:31:15,780 --> 01:31:17,519
Seriously... I can't even drink.

1299
01:31:17,520 --> 01:31:19,679
Being stuck between them is killing me.

1300
01:31:22,190 --> 01:31:23,670
What are you doing, you're a patient?

1301
01:31:24,440 --> 01:31:25,060
If you drink,

1302
01:31:25,061 --> 01:31:27,203
your wife said she'd kill me too.

1303
01:31:28,635 --> 01:31:30,328
She's thorough, so thorough.

1304
01:31:31,079 --> 01:31:33,000
My ideal type isn't a thorough woman.

1305
01:31:33,056 --> 01:31:35,031
So your ideal type is a scatterbrain?

1306
01:31:35,056 --> 01:31:36,664
Someone a bit clumsy.

1307
01:31:37,954 --> 01:31:38,954
What about you?

1308
01:31:39,946 --> 01:31:40,946
Me?

1309
01:31:43,625 --> 01:31:44,625
For me...

1310
01:31:45,007 --> 01:31:46,730
a sexy Spaniard.

1311
01:31:47,220 --> 01:31:49,007
A passionate Latino!

1312
01:31:49,203 --> 01:31:50,265
That's it.

1313
01:31:50,290 --> 01:31:52,640
Spanish pronunciation is so sexy.

1314
01:31:53,063 --> 01:31:55,578
I want to live somewhere sunny like Spain

1315
01:31:55,603 --> 01:31:58,296
with a gorgeous Latino man.

1316
01:31:59,132 --> 01:32:00,132
Cheers!

1317
01:32:00,210 --> 01:32:01,265
Cheers.

1318
01:32:03,587 --> 01:32:05,407
Maybe I should learn Spanish.

1319
01:32:30,230 --> 01:32:31,484
We're here.

1320
01:32:39,763 --> 01:32:40,763
Right now,

1321
01:32:41,210 --> 01:32:42,289
this isn't a dream, is it?

1322
01:32:42,314 --> 01:32:43,314
Of course not.

1323
01:32:45,616 --> 01:32:46,757
Should we sober up a bit

1324
01:32:46,782 --> 01:32:47,882
before we go in?

1325
01:32:50,710 --> 01:32:51,710
Okay.

1326
01:32:52,281 --> 01:32:53,703
You go in first.

1327
01:33:21,610 --> 01:33:22,890
I told you not to drink so much.

1328
01:33:23,046 --> 01:33:25,039
Didn't you say we should
drink together sometime?

1329
01:33:25,320 --> 01:33:27,640
I meant just the two of us.

1330
01:33:28,726 --> 01:33:30,359
Are you two still arguing?

1331
01:33:32,531 --> 01:33:34,031
You're certainly early.

1332
01:33:34,056 --> 01:33:35,685
Great timing.

1333
01:33:35,710 --> 01:33:36,565
What?

1334
01:33:36,590 --> 01:33:37,560
What do you mean, great timing?

1335
01:33:37,561 --> 01:33:38,796
What? Tell me!

1336
01:33:39,515 --> 01:33:40,385
He's drunk.

1337
01:33:40,410 --> 01:33:41,351
He's a goner.

1338
01:33:41,376 --> 01:33:42,376
Good work.

1339
01:33:45,375 --> 01:33:46,398
Hi, everyone.

1340
01:33:46,945 --> 01:33:48,025
Oh, Won-young, you're here?

1341
01:33:48,114 --> 01:33:49,114
Won-young.

1342
01:33:49,656 --> 01:33:50,845
Seriously.

1343
01:33:53,158 --> 01:33:53,778
Hmm?

1344
01:33:54,023 --> 01:33:55,023
Is Tae-jun here?

1345
01:33:55,548 --> 01:33:56,453
Won-young, you're here too?

1346
01:33:56,560 --> 01:33:57,570
Hyung, I'm here.

1347
01:33:57,648 --> 01:33:58,940
What do you mean, you're here?

1348
01:33:59,000 --> 01:34:01,039
Hey, you're late, so come and help.

1349
01:34:01,775 --> 01:34:02,671
Wait a second.

1350
01:34:02,696 --> 01:34:03,696
Okay.

1351
01:34:07,375 --> 01:34:09,125
Wait a second.

1352
01:34:10,429 --> 01:34:11,890
What's with the atmosphere?

1353
01:34:12,370 --> 01:34:13,970
Did you two decide to get back together?

1354
01:34:16,095 --> 01:34:17,765
It still doesn't feel real,

1355
01:34:19,101 --> 01:34:20,230
but finally,

1356
01:34:20,720 --> 01:34:22,560
thinking that I don't
have to be a spy anymore

1357
01:34:22,828 --> 01:34:24,050
is such a relief.

1358
01:34:26,587 --> 01:34:28,476
You two really took the long way around.

1359
01:34:29,109 --> 01:34:30,210
Look who's talking.

1360
01:34:30,453 --> 01:34:31,773
You're still traveling the world.

1361
01:34:32,383 --> 01:34:33,468
Now get out of the way.

1362
01:34:34,340 --> 01:34:36,359
Steak's here.

1363
01:34:37,730 --> 01:34:39,311
You're the one who saved my husband, right?

1364
01:34:39,335 --> 01:34:40,055
Hello.

1365
01:34:40,281 --> 01:34:41,610
It wasn't that much...

1366
01:34:41,635 --> 01:34:42,635
Eat up.

1367
01:34:42,784 --> 01:34:45,584
I saved the best cut
just for you, Won-young.

1368
01:34:45,914 --> 01:34:46,670
Thank you.

1369
01:34:46,695 --> 01:34:47,703
I'll enjoy it.

1370
01:34:54,031 --> 01:34:55,431
If you don't want to eat it, don't.

1371
01:34:55,860 --> 01:34:56,505
It's burnt.

1372
01:34:56,530 --> 01:34:57,530
Yun Tae-jun.

1373
01:34:57,555 --> 01:34:59,745
People call this well-done.

1374
01:34:59,986 --> 01:35:00,986
Don't they?

1375
01:35:07,945 --> 01:35:08,945
It's delicious.

1376
01:35:09,795 --> 01:35:10,995
You should try some too, Boss.

1377
01:35:13,303 --> 01:35:15,203
Tae-jun, you never eat anything burnt...

1378
01:35:22,540 --> 01:35:23,202
It's actually good...

1379
01:35:23,227 --> 01:35:24,227
He actually ate it.

1380
01:35:26,039 --> 01:35:27,593
How people change.

1381
01:35:30,507 --> 01:35:31,437
Honey.

1382
01:35:31,498 --> 01:35:33,906
How could you take off your wedding ring?

1383
01:35:34,203 --> 01:35:36,021
I just took it off for a
second while cooking.

1384
01:35:36,045 --> 01:35:36,943
For a second?

1385
01:35:36,968 --> 01:35:37,905
There's no such thing as "for a second."

1386
01:35:37,930 --> 01:35:38,720
This isn't just a ring.

1387
01:35:38,721 --> 01:35:40,225
It's a symbol of our love.

1388
01:35:40,250 --> 01:35:42,335
Wearing this is what keeps us connected.

1389
01:35:42,360 --> 01:35:43,435
Okay, stop lecturing me.

1390
01:35:43,460 --> 01:35:45,750
I put it back on, didn't I?

1391
01:35:46,607 --> 01:35:47,607
Don't ever take it off.

1392
01:35:48,680 --> 01:35:49,680
Promise me.

1393
01:35:49,889 --> 01:35:50,889
The ring promise.

1394
01:35:54,188 --> 01:35:55,188
Seal it.

1395
01:35:59,388 --> 01:36:00,388
Eat up.

1396
01:36:00,413 --> 01:36:01,218
Eat up.

1397
01:36:01,289 --> 01:36:02,816
Ah, I should have a
drink on a day like this.

1398
01:36:02,840 --> 01:36:04,562
Okay, let's all have a toast.

1399
01:36:04,587 --> 01:36:06,812
Cheers!

1400
01:36:08,645 --> 01:36:10,023
Did you hear about Ji Won-young?

1401
01:36:10,160 --> 01:36:10,867
What about him?

1402
01:36:11,038 --> 01:36:12,711
About him taking
kickbacks with Manager Kim.

1403
01:36:12,735 --> 01:36:14,186
I heard he used to be a
manager in the Finance team.

1404
01:36:14,210 --> 01:36:15,210
Oh my god.

1405
01:36:15,365 --> 01:36:16,675
So he was framed?

1406
01:36:16,700 --> 01:36:17,700
Yeah.

1407
01:36:17,725 --> 01:36:18,790
I heard after Manager Kim confessed,

1408
01:36:18,814 --> 01:36:20,257
he was reinstated immediately.

1409
01:36:20,520 --> 01:36:21,984
That's so unfair for him.

1410
01:36:22,009 --> 01:36:23,281
I know, right?

1411
01:36:24,140 --> 01:36:25,492
Where did you hear that?

1412
01:36:26,410 --> 01:36:27,265
I...

1413
01:36:27,422 --> 01:36:28,715
I'm asking who told you that.

1414
01:36:28,864 --> 01:36:30,095
I heard it from...

1415
01:36:30,120 --> 01:36:31,312
someone in HR.

1416
01:36:33,434 --> 01:36:35,335
I'm sorry about everything.

1417
01:36:53,536 --> 01:36:54,536
Won-young...

1418
01:36:55,609 --> 01:36:57,176
aren't you being a bit too
casual about coming and going?

1419
01:36:57,200 --> 01:36:58,671
The reason for my reinstatement...

1420
01:36:59,645 --> 01:37:01,101
does it really have to do

1421
01:37:01,830 --> 01:37:03,230
with the contract with Yun Tae-jun?

1422
01:37:04,420 --> 01:37:05,639
Why bring that up now?

1423
01:37:06,510 --> 01:37:07,120
You got your job back, didn't you?

1424
01:37:07,120 --> 01:37:08,120
Isn't that enough?

1425
01:37:15,557 --> 01:37:17,197
You never intended to report it, did you?

1426
01:37:17,981 --> 01:37:19,460
You were just using me.

1427
01:37:20,240 --> 01:37:21,560
After everything that's happened,

1428
01:37:22,070 --> 01:37:23,070
did you really expect me

1429
01:37:23,250 --> 01:37:25,390
to suddenly start acting with a conscience?

1430
01:37:25,499 --> 01:37:27,132
This isn't some college club.

1431
01:37:28,549 --> 01:37:30,023
I've noticed

1432
01:37:30,838 --> 01:37:32,726
that people like you

1433
01:37:33,730 --> 01:37:36,170
always blame others after
getting the short end of the stick.

1434
01:37:38,187 --> 01:37:39,657
It's because you're too weak.

1435
01:37:40,182 --> 01:37:42,821
You never stop to think if you
did anything wrong yourself.

1436
01:37:47,765 --> 01:37:48,990
About the pottery class,

1437
01:37:49,710 --> 01:37:51,085
I got the artist's approval.

1438
01:37:52,101 --> 01:37:53,312
I'll be handling it.

1439
01:38:15,400 --> 01:38:17,078
(I think I just saw you, Won-young.)

1440
01:38:17,661 --> 01:38:19,341
(When are you coming out of the restroom?)

1441
01:38:20,570 --> 01:38:21,620
(I'll be right out.)

1442
01:38:24,890 --> 01:38:26,320
So you're a Taepyeong employee.

1443
01:38:32,635 --> 01:38:35,335
Are you trying to suck up to
Tae-jun to get a promotion?

1444
01:38:42,547 --> 01:38:43,547
Don't waste your time.

1445
01:38:44,161 --> 01:38:46,161
I've already tried that method.

1446
01:38:46,414 --> 01:38:47,950
What are you trying to say?

1447
01:38:47,975 --> 01:38:48,975
Well,

1448
01:38:49,788 --> 01:38:51,045
I just can't stand to watch.

1449
01:38:51,230 --> 01:38:52,300
As you can see,

1450
01:38:52,325 --> 01:38:53,718
I'm working right now.

1451
01:38:55,382 --> 01:38:56,956
I don't have time to care about
what you can or can't stand.

1452
01:38:56,980 --> 01:38:58,789
Having someone seemingly
perfect say they like you

1453
01:38:58,790 --> 01:39:00,030
must make you feel pretty good.

1454
01:39:01,127 --> 01:39:02,445
Like you're someone special too.

1455
01:39:03,830 --> 01:39:05,117
Because I felt that way once.

1456
01:39:18,359 --> 01:39:19,480
You don't seem to realize.

1457
01:39:19,636 --> 01:39:21,576
If Yun Tae-jun has only one weakness,

1458
01:39:21,601 --> 01:39:22,695
it's me.

1459
01:39:24,679 --> 01:39:25,410
Not you.

1460
01:39:25,435 --> 01:39:27,492
I think you've got it wrong.

1461
01:39:28,315 --> 01:39:30,265
I'm not Yun Tae-jun's weakness,

1462
01:39:30,290 --> 01:39:31,609
and I have no desire to be.

1463
01:39:31,634 --> 01:39:33,154
Becoming someone's weakness...

1464
01:39:33,731 --> 01:39:35,601
I guess that's your way of loving someone.

1465
01:39:35,875 --> 01:39:37,395
Why would you want to be a weakness

1466
01:39:37,420 --> 01:39:39,260
and a stumbling block
for the person you love?

1467
01:39:41,117 --> 01:39:42,350
Is it because if you don't,

1468
01:39:42,921 --> 01:39:45,161
you don't have the confidence
to keep them by your side?

1469
01:39:45,730 --> 01:39:47,007
Normal people

1470
01:39:47,509 --> 01:39:48,796
don't love like that.

1471
01:39:51,125 --> 01:39:52,562
You guy...

1472
01:40:00,628 --> 01:40:01,628
Don't touch him.

1473
01:40:04,774 --> 01:40:05,910
Let's go.

1474
01:40:07,157 --> 01:40:09,173
I have a meeting in ten minutes.

1475
01:40:25,710 --> 01:40:26,438
Are you hurt?

1476
01:40:26,463 --> 01:40:27,876
It's just what you saw.

1477
01:40:27,901 --> 01:40:28,560
I'm sorry...

1478
01:40:28,585 --> 01:40:29,736
Why are you apologizing, Boss?

1479
01:40:29,760 --> 01:40:31,095
I really didn't think

1480
01:40:31,567 --> 01:40:32,688
he'd go looking for you

1481
01:40:33,001 --> 01:40:34,230
and provoke you like that.

1482
01:40:34,446 --> 01:40:36,282
I knew he was around,

1483
01:40:37,490 --> 01:40:38,490
but I didn't do anything.

1484
01:40:39,557 --> 01:40:40,774
I think I provoked him

1485
01:40:41,061 --> 01:40:42,899
more than he provoked me.

1486
01:40:56,360 --> 01:40:57,360
What are you... doing?

1487
01:40:57,385 --> 01:40:58,385
Nothing.

1488
01:41:03,388 --> 01:41:04,563
Mr. Yun, you're here?

1489
01:41:05,321 --> 01:41:06,321
Hello...

1490
01:41:09,102 --> 01:41:10,102
This way, please.

1491
01:41:14,325 --> 01:41:15,907
Let me know once you've checked this.

1492
01:41:16,090 --> 01:41:17,090
Okay.

1493
01:41:32,058 --> 01:41:33,058
Did you see that?

1494
01:41:33,083 --> 01:41:34,443
Ji Won-young from General Affairs.

1495
01:41:35,883 --> 01:41:38,767
It's amazing he can still come
to work with a smile like that.

1496
01:41:39,317 --> 01:41:41,978
If it were me, I'd be furious.

1497
01:41:42,321 --> 01:41:45,360
I know, right? He was cleared
of all charges and reinstated,

1498
01:41:45,608 --> 01:41:47,620
but people still say he's only
here because of connections.

1499
01:41:47,651 --> 01:41:49,971
I thought it was because of
his relationship with Mr. Yun.

1500
01:41:53,876 --> 01:41:55,626
Tell me more about that!

1501
01:42:09,009 --> 01:42:10,009
Boss.

1502
01:42:10,096 --> 01:42:11,136
Sorry to keep you waiting.

1503
01:42:22,163 --> 01:42:23,163
Why

1504
01:42:23,907 --> 01:42:25,021
didn't you quit?

1505
01:42:25,046 --> 01:42:25,938
What do you mean...

1506
01:42:25,963 --> 01:42:27,923
I heard everything from HR.

1507
01:42:29,431 --> 01:42:31,188
Even after hearing all those rumors,

1508
01:42:31,870 --> 01:42:33,946
what's the reason you're
still staying at the company?

1509
01:42:33,970 --> 01:42:34,630
What is it?

1510
01:42:34,630 --> 01:42:35,630
That's because...

1511
01:42:35,735 --> 01:42:36,809
because I have to be at the company

1512
01:42:36,810 --> 01:42:38,110
to see you, Boss.

1513
01:42:38,135 --> 01:42:39,015
I'm so sorry.

1514
01:42:39,040 --> 01:42:39,820
Boss,

1515
01:42:40,064 --> 01:42:41,290
you don't need to be sorry.

1516
01:42:41,315 --> 01:42:42,993
I just want you

1517
01:42:43,018 --> 01:42:46,392
to understand my guilt a little.

1518
01:42:46,923 --> 01:42:48,322
If I'd known you'd be treated like this,

1519
01:42:48,346 --> 01:42:49,415
I would never...

1520
01:42:49,527 --> 01:42:51,487
have accepted Manager
Jeong's proposal so easily.

1521
01:43:02,178 --> 01:43:03,178
Boss.

1522
01:43:03,203 --> 01:43:04,203
Look at me.

1523
01:43:06,022 --> 01:43:07,022
I

1524
01:43:07,626 --> 01:43:08,906
Don't care what other people do.

1525
01:43:09,159 --> 01:43:10,345
They can't hurt me.

1526
01:43:11,460 --> 01:43:13,243
The only thing that can scare me now

1527
01:43:13,735 --> 01:43:15,368
is you, Boss.

1528
01:43:36,079 --> 01:43:37,079
This...

1529
01:43:37,760 --> 01:43:39,204
how do you use it?

1530
01:43:39,587 --> 01:43:41,071
You just need to create an account.

1531
01:43:42,926 --> 01:43:44,563
Only4___

1532
01:43:45,445 --> 01:43:46,615
wy

1533
01:43:46,640 --> 01:43:48,446
Only4___wy?

1534
01:43:49,409 --> 01:43:50,409
Mine is

1535
01:43:50,434 --> 01:43:52,509
only4___tj

1536
01:43:53,202 --> 01:43:54,202
tj?

1537
01:43:55,419 --> 01:43:56,513
Tae-jun.

1538
01:43:58,860 --> 01:43:59,860
This kind of thing

1539
01:44:00,199 --> 01:44:01,679
is more fun when it's a bit childish.

1540
01:44:01,935 --> 01:44:03,640
Set it to private.

1541
01:44:05,193 --> 01:44:06,193
There.

1542
01:44:06,312 --> 01:44:07,312
Here you go.

1543
01:44:10,005 --> 01:44:11,296
Did you really want to use this that badly?

1544
01:44:11,320 --> 01:44:12,631
It has that feeling of being public

1545
01:44:12,655 --> 01:44:14,427
yet mysterious at the same time.

1546
01:44:15,566 --> 01:44:16,566
But

1547
01:44:16,692 --> 01:44:18,786
is there anything you
want to do with me, Boss?

1548
01:44:25,368 --> 01:44:27,038
Watch the sunset at the beach.

1549
01:44:28,035 --> 01:44:29,035
The sunset?

1550
01:44:29,060 --> 01:44:30,497
When you watch the sunset,

1551
01:44:31,641 --> 01:44:33,450
it feels like time

1552
01:44:33,475 --> 01:44:34,544
has stopped.

1553
01:44:40,096 --> 01:44:41,096
What do you think?

1554
01:44:42,323 --> 01:44:44,043
It kind of looks like a sunset, doesn't it?

1555
01:44:44,910 --> 01:44:45,910
Boss.

1556
01:44:46,068 --> 01:44:47,091
Look.

1557
01:44:48,177 --> 01:44:49,583
It does look a bit like it.

1558
01:44:56,961 --> 01:44:57,961
Boss,

1559
01:45:04,700 --> 01:45:06,560
you're really bad at reading the room.

1560
01:45:08,048 --> 01:45:09,048
What did you say?

1561
01:45:20,153 --> 01:45:21,536
Did you just realize that?

1562
01:45:23,490 --> 01:45:24,519
If I don't say anything,

1563
01:45:24,520 --> 01:45:26,360
you'll probably spend
the whole night on this.

1564
01:45:34,864 --> 01:45:36,919
Boss, you should wear it as a necklace.

1565
01:45:40,044 --> 01:45:41,560
In case people ask.

1566
01:45:55,216 --> 01:45:56,216
No way.

1567
01:45:59,187 --> 01:46:00,667
I'm going to show it off to everyone.

1568
01:46:19,044 --> 01:46:20,404
I really don't want to go to work.

1569
01:46:21,000 --> 01:46:22,000
I just want

1570
01:46:22,025 --> 01:46:23,591
to keep holding you like this.

1571
01:46:23,796 --> 01:46:25,196
If you don't want to go, then quit.

1572
01:46:25,757 --> 01:46:27,911
Oh, I can't do that.

1573
01:46:28,102 --> 01:46:29,742
You have to do things you hate sometimes.

1574
01:46:29,802 --> 01:46:30,931
You can't only do things you like.

1575
01:46:30,955 --> 01:46:33,458
You can't only do things you like,

1576
01:46:34,243 --> 01:46:35,443
but the things you WANT to do,

1577
01:46:36,157 --> 01:46:37,557
I'll make sure you can do them all.

1578
01:46:41,380 --> 01:46:42,380
Am I that easy to fool?

1579
01:46:43,179 --> 01:46:44,619
Just hearing you say that is enough.

1580
01:46:45,937 --> 01:46:47,843
Since you have a rich lover,

1581
01:46:48,720 --> 01:46:49,720
you should enjoy it.

1582
01:46:51,941 --> 01:46:52,941
That's a good point.

1583
01:46:53,770 --> 01:46:54,770
I'm kidding.

1584
01:46:55,095 --> 01:46:56,281
I'm serious.

1585
01:46:56,617 --> 01:46:57,617
I want you,

1586
01:46:58,210 --> 01:47:00,281
Won-young, to use me as much as you can.

1587
01:47:00,844 --> 01:47:01,844
Because I'm

1588
01:47:02,994 --> 01:47:04,394
already prepared to be used by you.

1589
01:47:05,070 --> 01:47:06,390
I'm not going to use you.

1590
01:47:08,059 --> 01:47:09,059
That's a shame.

1591
01:47:10,706 --> 01:47:11,706
I'll love you.

1592
01:47:19,232 --> 01:47:20,232
I just want

1593
01:47:21,570 --> 01:47:22,740
to love you properly.

1594
01:48:06,554 --> 01:48:09,500
I'm so sleepy... what are we doing?

1595
01:48:09,525 --> 01:48:11,125
Come, this way.

1596
01:48:20,420 --> 01:48:21,420
Sit here.

1597
01:48:22,742 --> 01:48:23,920
What are all these?

1598
01:48:24,161 --> 01:48:25,161
What do you mean?

1599
01:48:25,186 --> 01:48:26,186
It's breakfast.

1600
01:48:27,687 --> 01:48:29,390
Did you prepare this, Boss?

1601
01:48:30,855 --> 01:48:31,855
I wanted to cook for you.

1602
01:48:33,773 --> 01:48:34,840
Thanks for the food.

1603
01:48:35,193 --> 01:48:37,125
But... I can't guarantee it'll be good.

1604
01:48:46,120 --> 01:48:47,203
Well, it's not

1605
01:48:47,271 --> 01:48:48,703
as good as I imagined.

1606
01:48:58,841 --> 01:48:59,841
Don't eat it.

1607
01:48:59,866 --> 01:49:01,321
This isn't even fit for human consumption.

1608
01:49:01,345 --> 01:49:02,968
I'm going to eat it all.

1609
01:49:02,993 --> 01:49:04,873
Don't eat it, Boss.
I'm going to finish it all.

1610
01:49:10,378 --> 01:49:12,164
- Boss...
- Are you going to call me Boss...

1611
01:49:13,639 --> 01:49:15,429
forever?

1612
01:49:19,561 --> 01:49:20,561
Tae-jun hyung.

1613
01:49:23,160 --> 01:49:24,160
Give it to me.

1614
01:49:30,870 --> 01:49:33,234
I followed the recipe exactly,

1615
01:49:33,774 --> 01:49:34,633
but I couldn't get the taste right.

1616
01:49:34,658 --> 01:49:35,984
Tae-jun hyung, you're amazing.

1617
01:49:37,001 --> 01:49:38,593
How can it be this bad?

1618
01:49:40,610 --> 01:49:42,270
- Stop eating it.
- No, don't take it.

1619
01:49:42,295 --> 01:49:43,295
I'm going to eat it all.

1620
01:49:43,661 --> 01:49:44,828
I told you to stop.

1621
01:49:45,358 --> 01:49:46,609
Just drink some milk.

1622
01:49:48,210 --> 01:49:49,570
Then you stop eating it too, Boss.

1623
01:49:52,650 --> 01:49:53,650
Give it to me.

1624
01:50:08,100 --> 01:50:09,860
What are you doing not
answering your phone?

1625
01:50:11,837 --> 01:50:13,258
Are you finally awake?

1626
01:50:16,804 --> 01:50:17,804
Passion...

1627
01:50:18,472 --> 01:50:19,752
abrasadora!
(Burning passion!)

1628
01:50:20,990 --> 01:50:21,990
What's wrong with you?

1629
01:50:22,160 --> 01:50:23,160
Nothing.

1630
01:50:23,460 --> 01:50:25,275
That hysterical thing or whatever,

1631
01:50:25,300 --> 01:50:26,789
don't they speak Spanish?

1632
01:50:29,640 --> 01:50:30,631
(Introduction to Spanish)

1633
01:50:30,656 --> 01:50:32,676
You've really lost it.

1634
01:50:35,086 --> 01:50:36,240
Spanish?

1635
01:50:36,520 --> 01:50:37,843
What Spanish?

1636
01:50:38,140 --> 01:50:39,140
Seriously.

1637
01:50:39,568 --> 01:50:42,273
I thought you were studying
for the civil service exam...

1638
01:50:44,742 --> 01:50:46,531
Wait... wait... wait a second.

1639
01:50:55,870 --> 01:50:58,360
(Do you want to date me?)

1640
01:50:59,180 --> 01:51:00,945
Why haven't you left yet?

1641
01:51:02,342 --> 01:51:03,342
You understood that?

1642
01:51:05,875 --> 01:51:06,930
(Very good!)

1643
01:51:09,218 --> 01:51:10,390
Never mind.

1644
01:51:26,780 --> 01:51:27,780
Why...

1645
01:51:28,337 --> 01:51:29,679
why aren't you hitting me?

1646
01:51:33,522 --> 01:51:34,522
Hey.

1647
01:51:34,909 --> 01:51:36,305
Stop taking mine.

1648
01:51:36,330 --> 01:51:38,008
Eat your own, seriously.

1649
01:51:38,825 --> 01:51:40,101
Just let me do this one thing.

1650
01:51:44,967 --> 01:51:45,967
This one thing,

1651
01:51:48,869 --> 01:51:49,875
I'll let you do.

1652
01:52:03,060 --> 01:52:05,620
(Tae-jun hyung: I'm planning
to pull another all-nighter today.)

1653
01:52:06,600 --> 01:52:07,600
(Tae-jun hyung: Not me.)

1654
01:52:07,625 --> 01:52:09,062
(Tae-jun hyung: It's that old man.)

1655
01:52:13,515 --> 01:52:16,562
(Sigh... I'm so jealous of that old man.)

1656
01:52:17,180 --> 01:52:20,410
(I want to see you too, hyung.)

1657
01:52:26,560 --> 01:52:28,120
Is there something I can help you with?

1658
01:52:29,304 --> 01:52:30,600
Won-young, can we

1659
01:52:31,780 --> 01:52:33,422
talk for a moment?

1660
01:52:38,137 --> 01:52:39,359
I'm quite busy.

1661
01:52:40,860 --> 01:52:42,140
Listen, Won-young.

1662
01:52:42,804 --> 01:52:43,930
Something big has happened.

1663
01:52:44,453 --> 01:52:45,690
Mr. Yun

1664
01:52:45,828 --> 01:52:47,803
notified us that he wants
to terminate the contract.

1665
01:52:47,827 --> 01:52:50,254
- What do you mean?
- The signing bonus was hundreds of millions.

1666
01:52:50,279 --> 01:52:51,610
The penalty is three times that.

1667
01:52:51,953 --> 01:52:53,900
But he said he doesn't care.

1668
01:52:53,925 --> 01:52:55,351
He said he'll pay it all.

1669
01:52:56,392 --> 01:52:57,392
Ah, seriously.

1670
01:52:58,238 --> 01:53:00,628
But the Chairman said the
reason for the termination

1671
01:53:01,143 --> 01:53:02,143
is because of me.

1672
01:53:02,235 --> 01:53:03,235
Have you heard anything?

1673
01:53:05,467 --> 01:53:08,281
If I'd known you'd be
treated like this, I would never

1674
01:53:08,500 --> 01:53:10,460
have accepted Manager
Jeong's proposal so easily.

1675
01:53:11,060 --> 01:53:12,234
I want you,

1676
01:53:12,640 --> 01:53:14,858
Won-young, to use me as much as you can.

1677
01:53:16,977 --> 01:53:18,164
Because I'm

1678
01:53:19,281 --> 01:53:20,718
already prepared to be used by you.

1679
01:53:22,289 --> 01:53:23,289
Tae-jun hyung.

1680
01:53:23,448 --> 01:53:24,632
Won-young, you're

1681
01:53:25,177 --> 01:53:26,914
pretty close with Mr. Yun, aren't you?

1682
01:53:27,171 --> 01:53:28,421
Can you find out what's going on?

1683
01:53:28,445 --> 01:53:29,520
Actually, I

1684
01:53:29,545 --> 01:53:32,132
went to Gangneung three days in a row
to beg him to see me,

1685
01:53:32,157 --> 01:53:34,054
but he wouldn't even look at me.

1686
01:53:36,550 --> 01:53:38,600
My job is on the line here.

1687
01:53:40,382 --> 01:53:41,480
Should I

1688
01:53:42,800 --> 01:53:43,800
look into it for you?

1689
01:53:44,216 --> 01:53:45,216
Really?

1690
01:53:46,410 --> 01:53:47,410
You'll really help me?

1691
01:53:48,273 --> 01:53:49,590
Please, Won-young.

1692
01:53:49,615 --> 01:53:50,615
Please save me.

1693
01:53:54,203 --> 01:53:56,093
I'm not doing this to
save you, Manager Jeong.

1694
01:53:56,289 --> 01:53:58,031
If I bring Mr. Yun back,

1695
01:53:58,590 --> 01:53:59,929
it'll be my achievement,

1696
01:54:00,156 --> 01:54:01,400
not yours.

1697
01:54:02,180 --> 01:54:02,766
What?

1698
01:54:02,791 --> 01:54:04,591
I'm giving you a chance
to make things right.

1699
01:54:05,328 --> 01:54:07,208
And you need to formally
report to the Chairman

1700
01:54:07,747 --> 01:54:09,437
that Yun Tae-jun's exclusive contract

1701
01:54:09,828 --> 01:54:11,348
was all my doing from start to finish.

1702
01:54:12,359 --> 01:54:14,554
- That's a bit...
- And before that,

1703
01:54:16,180 --> 01:54:17,492
you need to apologize to me.

1704
01:54:18,399 --> 01:54:20,054
- Sincerely.
- What did you say?

1705
01:54:23,328 --> 01:54:25,421
Don't give me that.

1706
01:54:25,929 --> 01:54:27,369
You two already had a falling out.

1707
01:54:27,370 --> 01:54:28,106
I know all about it.

1708
01:54:28,131 --> 01:54:29,541
Then just quit.

1709
01:54:30,432 --> 01:54:32,117
Whatever happens to you in the end,

1710
01:54:32,505 --> 01:54:33,665
it has nothing to do with me.

1711
01:54:35,950 --> 01:54:37,484
Uh... I'm sorry.

1712
01:54:45,830 --> 01:54:46,830
I'm really sorry,

1713
01:54:47,848 --> 01:54:48,848
Mr. Ji Won-young.

1714
01:55:20,380 --> 01:55:21,380
But anyway,

1715
01:55:21,566 --> 01:55:23,446
is there anything you
want to do with me, Boss?

1716
01:55:24,367 --> 01:55:26,257
Watch the sunset at the beach.

1717
01:55:26,481 --> 01:55:27,091
The sunset?

1718
01:55:27,310 --> 01:55:28,740
When you watch the sunset,

1719
01:55:28,962 --> 01:55:30,781
it feels like time

1720
01:55:30,913 --> 01:55:32,000
has stopped.

1721
01:55:42,828 --> 01:55:44,077
(Want to watch it together?)

1722
01:56:55,554 --> 01:56:56,685
Found you.

1723
01:56:56,710 --> 01:56:57,710
Thank you.

1724
01:56:57,992 --> 01:56:58,695
For what?

1725
01:56:58,720 --> 01:56:59,890
For everything.

1726
01:57:02,810 --> 01:57:03,810
Isn't that...

1727
01:57:04,192 --> 01:57:05,192
a bit cliché?

1728
01:57:07,044 --> 01:57:09,210
Then why don't you be creative?

1729
01:57:42,607 --> 01:57:43,607
I love you.

1730
01:58:05,051 --> 01:58:06,691
It really feels like time has stopped.

1731
01:58:08,676 --> 01:58:09,676
You're right.

1732
01:59:48,718 --> 01:59:54,343
Unintentional Love Story: The Movie
